column1: HeatMate 10,600 BTU Radiant Kerosene Heater HMN110
column4: ["I currently have a couple of these kerosene heaters and I like to rotate them out every so often, as to not let the wick from just one get all of the use over the winter season. I have never had any problem with this heater and I would never go thru a winter without a couple of them. I always try to have a back up to what I use the most of, so I won't be without one working, just in case. They put out excellent heat in my room size of 15' X 24'. Also great if the power ever was to go out for a while during cold times. When the heater is fired up and the mantle is all glowing without any flame going higher than the mantle, I notice very little kerosene smell. Mine have been a life saver over the years that I've owned them. Bruce; TN.", "I was not happy when I first got this heater.  The flame adjustment was only usable when it is in the all the way up position.  It should start out high and then after it mellows out you adjust it down.  Also the fumes were terrible!  I could not use it indoors.  I had tried it 3 times and would have sent it back but as it was heavy and a large box I just didn't want the hassle.  I pulled it off the back porch last night for one last try.  It worked great!  I stood right over it and inhaled and no fumes at all!  I was using K1 kero at 4.99 a gallon for indoor use.  So...it could be when a heater is new it has to burn a few tanks to get to where it needs to be.  I am satisfied now but still wish the wick came up higher...but it is a good heater...you just have to burn it off a few times.", 'Work great no fumes and heats up a room with a tin roof and cement floor real good', 'Heater is amazing. Heats my living room very fast. Made very well. Great value. Great product. ', 'Great heater, I burn #1 stove oil instead of expensive Kerosene and no smell at all.', "Haven't used it yet, but it arrived quickly, and looks great!", 'This is my second season using it. I only used it a handful of times last year and it constantly shut itself of. mI not sure of the problem but wic is good and it just doesnt work wright. Feels warm when it works but unfortunatley mine has not,I plan to take it apart this weekend to find out the issue', 'I love it üëç', 'Just the part I needed. Well described.', 'I was and still am, very impressed. Nice design, easy to start, just a great product.']

column1: Cadet Com-Pak 2000-Watt 240-Volt Electric Wall Heater 67507
column4: ["It was replacing an aged wall heater that had finally given up the ghost. It was a 1500 watt model, but after installing the Com-Pak, that was only 1000 watts, it's output was higher. And it's construction was obviously of high higher quality.  And it is much quieter than old was, even when it was new. Only problem I had was it was slightly smaller to fit into the original hole in the wall.  Not the fault of the heater. I'm a bit of a handy-man so just shimmed the hole and trimmed it with some molding and it looks pretty good.", 'I have been dealing with electrical items and electricity for 60 years, andthis heater beats any I have ever dealt with. To be as small as it is, easy to mount,,but the most important thing is 2000 watts and only pulling 8.3 amps seems unreal. Most electric heaters 120 v, 1500 watts pull 12...I have just ordered another one and plan on another. A great item, ', 'Purchased five units to heat a few rooms in my vacation home and these were perfect. Very easy to install and works well. Has a built in thermostat.', "small and neat looking. easy to install (BUT WAS REPLACING A DIFFERENT UNIT, SO NO EXTRA WIRING WAS REQUIRED). don't know how it performs yet, as it's not cold out, but easy to operate.", 'Overheat protection device broke on my very similar older style unit.  New unit allowed me to use old mounting and grill after some cutting. New units do not have the same overheat protector.  New unit has much smaller grill which I did not need.', 'Powerful unit, yet small in size. Does exact what we got it for. Bath room early showers are comfortable now. We run it about 10 minutes.', 'The product arrived in excellent condition and performed as needed.  The correct wattages has kept the room very comfortable', 'Installed heater without any problems. It works like a charm!', 'The one I have stopped functioning, so I had to replace it with same.', 'I was very satisfied with this heater. The fan is very powerful and it heat up really fast. Really liked it. Yes I would recommendThis product.']

column1: 10 American Wick Kerosene Heater Wicks  #AW-500 NEW  Fits many perfection models
column4: ['I got these wicks for my antique Perfection kerosene heaters (I bought several more to keep on hand after trying two). In my opinion, this wick actually out-performs the (new old stock) Perfection Brand wicks available for sale, which can be smelly from age, sometimes bent or rusted, and the cotton wick material, itself, tends to be a bit stiff from age, and occasionally are reconditioned or simply moved in the carrier to appear to be new when they are, in fact, used. I\'ve had that result twice from buying "new" old stock Perfection Brand wicks. This American Wick AW-500 fits perfectly, works smoothly, and is made with superior materials and craftsmanship. The wick is all cotton, heavy-duty and is long-lasting. It\'s clean-burning and there is no smoke or odor. The steel wick carrier is sturdy and smooth. Unlike the Perfection Brand wick, the American AW-500 is constructed with 4 splits in the lower part which go into the tank, creating 4 "tails" (NOTE: The lower portion of the wick is not visible in photo, as they are tucked inside its own cylindrical carrier in packaging, and in the photo). The American Wick AW-500 wick is very similar to the Perfection Brand 500 wick, but the Perfection  wick is split in 2 places and has 2 tails. In my opinion, the American AW-500 wick with 4 tails works better and is easier to install, because the 4-way tail split allows the wick tales to be more easily maneuvered around the wick adjuster, to seat a bit lower when turned down, and the tails to dip deeper into the kerosene tank and are more neatly adjusted up and down without binding at all. The cost of this item is very reasonable and I think it\'s a great value, compared with the usually higher-priced original Perfection 500 wicks to be found for sale. I hesitated at first to buy this non-Perfection part for my Perfection heaters, but after a couple of bad experiences with the more costly Perfection wicks, I am so glad I took the chance and bought the American AW-500 wicks! I\'m extremely pleased! I highly recommend this excellent product! ', "These are not very heavy weight, the weave is loose, and they are not even close to the high quality brand name wick I order from England.  Cosmetically it's not nice looking as an original Perfection wick . Heavy metal wick sleeve is good and they are nicely fastened with metal riveting. They will work just fine in a Perfection 500 heater they just don't last as long as the other brand I buy and they will burn down a little bit faster.  If I can get a good deal on an AW-500 wick or this is the only one available it is much better than a fiberglass wick. Just make sure that you are gentle installing the wick and if one gets a lot of tar from contaminated fuel, moisture,  improper use,  and sticky in the wick gallery these will tear. Odor wise they will smell terrible when you burn one in for the first time that is normal because they are not pre charred. If you run at the highest flame setting possible in the Perfection 500  heater burning good quality kerosene they will do a good job. I use a Perfection 500 heater burning clear kerosene every day year round as my only source of heat and for cooking? If I can get a good deal on one or more of these AW500 wicks I will buy them.   ", 'Excellent quality.  AW-45 is lower part of a mechanical wick; AW-40 is the top part only; AW-49 is both top and bottom.  AW-45, as the bottom only, appears to be no longer available from wick manufacturers.  Grab them if you can find them!', 'Fits just as it should. Burns great in my Perfection M525 Heater. Will definitely buy again, although this one will last me for a few years.', 'Much better quality wick than even more expense wicks out there.  This one burns like the OEM all cotton wick with normal  charring as it should.  Other wicks I have used seem to have a high percentage of nylon or other synthetic and leave a hard residue after just one or two burns that is then hard to relight.  This wick has none of that and I will buy buy another just to have one hand. ', "I was skeptical to purchase at first, considering they don't manufacture the Perfection Heaters anymore, but I took a chance and was very happy this wick is quite similar to an original Perfection wick, and it's 100% cotton. The only issue I experienced was that the gear holes on the wick canister didn't exactly line up correctly. Fortunately I was able to transfer the wick to the original wick canister which has gear holes all around it, making it much easier to install.", 'I had to get another one because it had burned down. When I forget to turn off the heater, the wick will burn down one quarter of an inch each time. I probably will be ordering another soon. Thanks for the product and price.', 'Heater is 100yrs. old, was easy to install,glad wick was still available.', 'These were great! I have two 50 year old vintage kerosene heater and these worked out perfectly!! I highly recommend these!', "The next best thing to the 'Perfection' brand wick. Second one I bought. Very dependable."]

column1: Cadet 79241 120-Volt 1000 Watts 8.33 Amp Compact Electric Wall Heater
column4: ['it puts out a nice soft heat instead of a burning hot heat from those glowing hot coils. no hot coils just a nice soft fan blown heat . perfect for medium to small bathrooms or bedrooms. to me it take a ,little long to get it right  but it gets there and is very comfortable. perfect to replace those old thermadors..in many older bathrooms  I thought it was a little pricey but so is everything else.I also thought the grill and frame should have been one piece to keep all the edges straight when screwed in but that I think was my installer but none of my peeves is a deal breaker.   Forgot To mention you may need to purchase the wall can liner too.      ', 'This product was originally intended to replace the old existing wall heater with new vintage look.It does not fit properly in the old existing vintage space that it was created to replace.', "This is the heater to buy if you need a direct replacement for the old Thermador 100 / 101 radiant coil heater.Fits right in the in wall box - only difference is the switch will be at bottom, rather than at top. (At least that's how my old one was).This heater also has a fan, so heat gets pushed out into rom, so you don't have to stand RIGHT in front of it to get warm!!", 'It does what was expected of it from the research that was done. Installation was easy with the wall can. The chrome finish has always been an eye catcher for us. ', "Simple replacement for vintage model, it also has forced air so it blow's the heat to warm area much faster!", 'heater worked out fine,had to get different installation screws,what it came with all broke or stripped out cheap junk screws and clips.', 'it easy to install', 'Perfect fit as a replacement for a Thermador 101.Did not need to replace the mounting box or wiring.Easy DIY.', "Had to purchase the wall metal insert separately since product didn't come with it.  Operation not as quiet as other heaters we have."]

column1: Broan-NuTone 9093WH Exhaust Fan Heater and Light Combo Bathroom Ceiling Heate...
Electric Baseboard Heater Cadet 96 In. 2,000/2,500 Watt 240 Volt White Durable
column4: ["This heater is fairly large.  Don't expect it to fit under your legs in the bleachers.  The handle is really handy, but makes it pretty tall.This heater is very versatile. It can be like the smaller versions with just one element on at half power, full power, or both elements on full power.  It goes through propane about the same as all the other ones I've seen, and full power is a lot of power.  The fan (powered by D cells) blows warm air in your direction, which is nice because otherwise it just goes straight up.IMHO it's way handier than the smaller bottle mounted version because it doesn't tip easily and it's not as tall.  It puts the heat in a better location.It's not a small heater, but is powerful, well built, and looks like it will last.", 'this id the 2nd one I have owned  first one was 5 years old and used every day it was cold it keeps our coach warm enough on low  and very economicl to run do recomend getting the hose with regolator and using a 20 pound bbq grill tank outside  and keeping a couple of the one pound throw aways in reserve incase of a midnight run out of gas senero , teriffic for those emergencies and blizzards requires no electric to run just a couple batteries to run the fan but will still  produce  het with out fan not operating . has the o2 depletion piliot light that lifts off if o2 level gets to low plus tip switch incase it gets tipped over by accident , Like any heating device care should be taken to assure you are opperating it in a safe manner and following the instructions that states the clearences on ll sides ', 'Current house furnace is out and this unit has filled in amazingly well.  Live in MN and have 2 of these with a couple electric room heaters for 2000 sqft plus home and been heating for a month.  Do recommend the 20# Walmart propane tanks w/ gauge for $48 and conversion hose to unit for more economical heating that the small canisters.  CAn heat for nearly a week.  Have CO monitor and never have had it go off once.  They are made to be CO free .  We do not leave them running when not home for safety reason but never yet had an issue.  ', 'I bought this to be able to work in my 2 car garage during cold days. It works very well. The only drawback I could see is that the fan moves very little air. Otherwise, I would have given it a 5 star rating....  Made the garage able to be worked in with no jacket in about 2 hours (on a 15 degree day)  Well worth it...   And would be great thing to have if an ice storm hits and the power (heat) went out...  Costs less than a buck an hour worth of propane to run on High.  I bought a 15 lb tank and ran it for about 18 hours.....    I plan on getting a couple of portable 1 lb bottles and a refill adapter.....', 'Got Mr. Heater for a heater in my outside work area and as an emergency backup heater in case of power failure in a storm or the heat pump went bad in middle of winter. Works perfect and am using hooked up to 20lb propane tank and also little 1lb tanks. Either way is working perfect.  This thing will run you out of house on 18,000 btu setting.  Always vent from a window or door to keep oxygen fresh and will be good for indoor use, you will still be plenty warm and no worries about any pipes freezing. Great product', "This little heater is just the ticket for quickly warming up our home on those chilly mornings. ,I live where we seldom get any colder than 40 degrees at night , we don't run any heater at night for safety reasons ,although I feel this heater is safer than any electric one , no cords to overheat . I turn it on in the morning and in 15 minutes the chill is taken off the house. I use a small fan to circulate the heat more than the one that comes with the heater which is efficient for one room.  I also purchased the 12 foot hose and regulator so I can hook to a 30 lbs bottle out side the house. just ran the hose through an existing tv cable  hole. I can get about a week of heat out of one bottle at 16.00 to refill. That is much cheaper than running electric space heaters.", "The dogs and I have a very comfortable warm environment now that the heater is able to be used. They are so happy that the inside of the motorhome is a lot more comfortable. We have been having nights that are in the upper twenties and low 30s so we're really grateful to have a heater the prize this my cheat on low setting it it basically heats the Whole 30 ft motorhome it generates more than enough heat on low and will run for a hundred hours on that setting .  It is very warm at got my  farm in Coupeville Washington. thanks a lot for a great item!!", 'I\'ve been hunting deer for 42 years now and never worried about the cold weather when I was younger, mostly because pop-up portable blinds and portable heaters like these were not available back then. But my youngest daughter started hunting with me 6 years ago and after watching her brave a particularly cold opening day her first year I decided there had to be a better setup so she could enjoy going with me and I could insure I would get to continue to enjoy spending such moments with her, so I bought my first ground blind and my first Mr. Heater Little Buddy heater, and closing weekend of rifle season was soooooo much more enjoyable. Having a heat source to warm our feet made all the difference in the world being able to sit beside my daughter and just watch her scan our surroundings for her first deer, and did she take a beauty! After realizing how great the difference in the experience having shelter and heat made, I broke down and bought blinds for my Dad, nephew, and great friend who owns the property where we hunt, and then decided everyone should be able to stay warm and enjoy their time in the field as well, so I retired my Little Buddy heater and bought three of the Buddy heaters and one of the heater/cooker models and stocked each blind with a heater. The difference between the Little Buddy and the bigger Buddy models is very noticeably different! Running the bigger Buddy heaters warmed up a two person ground blind sufficiently enough to allow us to take off our coats, even with several windows open, and sit comfortably without creating undue noise or alerts to the deer as we watched many feed and browse around in the field in front of us. Hunting went from a cold and trying event to a greatly enjoyed experience spending time with my daughter, my Dad, my nephew, and friend! I\'ve always said a bad day hunting or fishing is better than a good day working anytime, but having Mr. Heater Buddy heaters warming our ground blinds has made such a difference in our time spent together so much more enjoyable that now my oldest daughter is joining in, and that alone made any expense paid for the equipment one of my best investments! Funny story: My Dad was using the heater I put in the blind he was using and after spending the morning hunting we all went to breakfast and I asked him how well he liked having heat, and his reply was, "great for about 20 minutes and then the damned thing quit and wouldn\'t re-light!" I asked him if he had opened any windows and he said "no, it wasn\'t light yet so I was just enjoying staying warm, until the heater went out!" I started laughing and he was taken aback by my reaction and asked why I was laughing, had I played a joke and given him the junk heater? I said no and told him he should be thankful Mr. Heater saved his life! Not knowing what I was referring to he had a puzzled look on his face, so I told him that the heater has a low oxygen sensor built into it and because he had the windows closed up fresh air could not circulate through the blind and the heater shut off before he could pass out from carbon monoxide poisoning! The look on his face was priceless! All he could say was "glad someone was looking out for him." After breakfast and getting some chores done we all went back to our blinds and my Dad made sure he opened some windows and lit the heater, and spent the rest of the day happy and warm. Moral of the story: The safety features built into Mr. Heater heaters work! Excellent design, quality built, and smart safety features all make Mr. Heater heaters great products you can trust and that make experiences during cold weather so much more enjoyable, and if having one gets a friend or family member to join in the fun, that\'s money well spent! Not to mention having the added insurance of staying warm at home should the power go out for an extended period of time during cold weather!   So, that\'s my experience with Mr. Heater heaters, and I can and do highly recommend to anyone needing and looking for a quality and dependable portable small heater, get one. You will be glad you did! ', 'Due to recently power outage frequently, I brought this protable heater for indoor use for emergency. I did not have chance to try it for hour long but I did try and find out it is very practical make and workable. Only issue to me is I don‚Äôt aware it need 4 D battery to run and how long one will last.Any how it is a very good product,I highly recommend it.', "Will be able to use it in my fish house, heat my area that I use for skinning and tanning the furs that I've trapped. column1: DeLonghi Mica Thermic Panel Heater, 2 Heat Settings, Black HMP1500 1500 Watts
column4: ["I like this heater a lot. I bought two of them. One I've mounted on my bedroom wall. The other I left on its wheels so I can move it around the house. And it does have a very comfortable recessed carrying handle. It does give off an offensive odor at the beginning, so I recommend placing it outside, running, for 3-4 hours and that should burn off the smell. It's very, very quiet but not totally silent. I has a slight audible hum, which I thought would bother me at first, but I've easily adjusted to it. In fact, I learned to find it comforting, like white noise. I find listening to its slight hum and feeling its warming comfort actually induces me to go to sleep. It's a radiant heater, but unlike the older type radiant heaters, it doesn't cook you. It has two settings. On Minimum (800 watts), only the top one third of the heater heats up. On Max (1500 watts), the entire heater heats up. It can heat up my 10' by 10' bedroom on a very cold day (around 32 degrees) within in an hour.  The only fault that I've found with this heater is that the automatic shut off alarm can kick in too soon, before the it's completed its job, but that happens only on Max. Otherwise, once I warm up my bedroom, I can run it on Minimum all night with no disturbing alarm. I've put it on a remote controlled timer switch that can be set to shut off at intervals of 2 hours, 4 hours, 6 hours, or longer. I do this to save electricity. Just be sure the timer you buy can handle more than 1500 watts. At the same time, it's also plugged into a remote controlled thermostat (available on eBay). I set the heater's thermostat to its highest setting, and let the remote thermostat control when the heater comes on and off.", 'warms quickly, feels healthy, large surface heat area. best heater so far. thanks', "I came to the conclusion that this heater would be a good pick for a bedroom. I ended up purchasing this DeLonghi Mica Panel Heater for the bedroom. The reason I chose this brand over other mica panels is due to my experience with their products in the past. I've owned a DeLonghi Radiator Heater which has worked just as great. If you dont know much about DeLonghi, they are a European-based company that makes quality appliances, specifically utilizing German-engineering.", 'I bought this heater to replace my oil filled radiator which stopped working. It is for a 12 foot by 12 foot bedroom. The old radiator heated the room comfortably but took a while to get up to heat. This new heater is more powerful and heats up quicker even though it is a 1500w heater just like the radiator was. Highly recommend for average sized rooms!', 'This is the best heater I‚Äôve ever used . With it anchored to wall much safer than most .', 'if you want a quite heater that will do the job over time even in a large under insulated areas this is your heater. remember it is a convection heater and may take time to bring the room up to desired temperature but this one really puts out the heat, great quality and modern looks I like you can mount on wall and none of the exposed areas will burn you.', 'Before use you should put outdoors and put it on max so the smell will burn off.  Happened indoors and was not a good thing.  It heats very well and is very quiet.', "Quiet.  Heats a room or my livingroom-diningroom-kitchen stretch with a heat that actually feels warm.  I have it on the lowest setting to do that.  Keep the thermostat at 60 and move the heater around to the main area of the house in the day and to the bedroom at night and don't need to heat the whole house all the time with the gas heat. Wish it had a handle on top to move it when it is warm.  Casters are plastic so we'll see how long that lasts but I am careful with my things.", 'We had a prior model and just love this one.  It took husband 5 minutes to install and puts out more heat than the original.  Thank you for sending product so quickly.', "The price was just right and it's a great fit"]

column1: Dr Infrared Portable Space Heater W/ Dual Heating System 1500 Watt Tans
column4: ["Pros-outside of unit not hot if you touch it.it's on wheels, cycles on to adjust set temperature, has a remote, has a timer, safety switches ( temp & if it tips over ). Youtube videos on how to repair unit, parts available. Looks nice, immediate heat, does not deplete oxygen like a ceramic heater, you can breath easily.Cons- 1500 watts & 12.5 amps power used. Monitor it when you first use it, a weak or bad electrical receptacle can arc! Your plug or power cord could melt or burn. The risk always exists when you use it. I use to do electrician work long ago, be mindful.Read all instructions thoroughly and completely! DO NOT LEAVE UNATTENDED! I still like to use this heater, in fact I own two of them. Follow all safety warnings, it can be a good heater, don't let your guard down.....be vigilant, be safe, and stay warm. I watch TV with one keeping me warm, and happy.", "Impressed with quality and many features like holding heat level economically, auto dual fan speeds, easy reading temperature, easy set up and great looking unit. Doesn't even look like a heater, more like a piece of furniture or a speaker for a high end stereo system.", 'I hen purchase several brands of infrared heaters .   Dr. Heater is built solid .  Purchased my last one in 2013.   Warranty is unsurpassed with 3 years .  Most heaters just won‚Äôt last .  Also puts our more heat output than a comparable EdenPure .   Good value and great  quality .', 'It is a hybrid infrared.  60% of the heat comes from a relatively new PTC heater.  40% comes from infrared.  It heats the air and objects in the room at the same time.  I have a small home of 1250 sq. ft.  I have three of these heaters at various places and have been able to shut my gas furnace down entirely.  Since they are very stingy on electricity, my monthly heating bill is now much less than it used to be!  I would recommend this heater to anyone without hesitation!', 'My Dr 968 1500 watt heater produces heat rapidly and cycles on and off to keep the temp where it is set.  This small unit has a fan that is barely audible and manages to push the heat away from the heat elements into the room and keep the area comfortable.  Lots of heat in a small package.', 'Well-built unit. Small, unobtrusive, and quiet. Easy to use with control panel or remote control, and the built-in thermostat works as it should. A nice feature is that the unit is on wheels so makes it easy to roll out of the way when cleaning and vacuuming. Takes the chill off my small place quite nicely. Great to use during those in-between seasons before or after you shut down or turn on the heating system. I am very satisfied with this product!', 'I have read a great deal of reviews from others before my first purchase. I have other brand spot heaters in my collection. Trial by error I suppose. Colorado Winters can be brutal at times. I purchased this for my mothers not well insulated home. a living room and a kitchen connected, 630 sq ft. this heater will keep it at a comfortable temp. for her. All at a low setting.Shuts off as it should to measure the heat in the room and comes back on when it needs to.It is supplemental. It will not heat a whole home.My unit arrived with a cracked frame on the top left corner. It works though, that is my main concern.Stays on five hours as i programmed and shuts off. Good Bang for the Buck. 5200 BTU is a great output for this size The fan is quiet when running. You can watch t.v. without noticing the heater on.In my opinion, if these units are used wisely, they are useful and can save a bit of money on your bill. Thumbs up on this unit.........', "I bought this to use in a bedroom because it was advertised as quiet, and it came with a remote.  It's not that quiet- just a little quieter than your average cheapo space heater.  And the remote doesn't power the heater on or off- just lets the unit go on standby, which is kind of a drag.  The standby light is so bright i wound up covering it with a piece of paper.  Except for the remote, it's not worth the money.", 'Despite the fact that the first heater stopped working after 4 years I purchased another, Reasons: great features, heats area very well, low cost to operate, compact and easy to move around', "Product arrived extremely quickly.  I'm using it in a sun-room to keep the temperatures steady for two parrots.  Am not able to determine if I am saving money on this product or not running it continuously versus other types of heating methods.  Product works well - happy so far."]

column1: Cyclonic Ceramic Heater with Fresh Air Ionizer and Remote Control
column4: ["this little heater will heat your small room to a toasty comfort level in just minutes, with the remote control everything is a snap and no need to get out of your seat, it is that easy to use, it's compact so it fits anywhere in a room giving you space, this product was a really good price,", "I love this heater. My wife dragged me to Lowe's to by a heater. I told her that we should buy a ceramic heater instead of a infrared heater. But like always she didn't want to listen. We ended up buying a heater for 150. This heater looks like old cast iron heater and it takes like an hour to make a room comfy. BBUUUUTTTT this Lasko heater is the BOMB and very worth it.", "Works like a champ.  This heats my 250 square foot garage that is like an ice cube, otherwise.  I really like the thermostat feature.  I've had two of these in the past, and they have always worked well.", "We have a small house in s.e. mich.. about 700 sq. ft. on the main level.  several years ago our furnace quit and we've been using ceramic heaters ever since.  I bought this lasco heater this fall to see if it could do better than the previous heater and it has been keeping the wholehouseat about 66 to 68 degrees so far.  Right now we are having the coldest below zero weather in years and it is still keeping things at around 60 with no other heater. needless to say, we have turned on an additional ceramic heater and the temp in the living room isaround 65. I repeat we have no other furnace or heater in the housethe basement stays around 60 all the time but as soon as the outdoors temps rise into the 20's and 30's it will be about 68 in here and we will only need the large Lasco heater.I am very happy with this heater.", 'Works well and looks like the picture, but not quite the remote I was looking for.  I understand the remote that actually went with my upright fan, the model is now out of date or for sale.', 'I plugged the space heaters in immediately and it took the chill right off the house love them. I have a heat pump and when the temperature gets below 32 the system needs help. These are perfect.', 'Quiet; Very powerful; Many fan & heat speed/temperature options. Delivered much faster than even my dog\'s favorite (E-bay) dog food! The back of this unit is not even the slightest bit warm, even when temperature and fan speed are at "max"! Greatly helps supplement our home\'s central heat, even during extremely cold weather.', "This heater warms my apartment way better than the heating sytem for the apartment. It's easy to move around and it does not get hot so you can move it without the danger of getting burned bu holding the sides. Good choice for anyone who has to use gas heat or heat a lot. Could save you a lot of money.", 'Actually, my 5/6 year old unit is STILL GOOD. but the remote died from battery corrosion.So, I now have TWO GOOD EXCELLENT HEATERS- with One REMOTE. * works on bothüëçüèª', "This heater provides a great deal of heat for a large room/ recommend it for purchase, if a person is interested a quality heater.....it's well worth the investment/ Thank you."]

column1: New LASKO 758000 Cyclonic Ceramic Heater
column4: ['The Lasko Cyclonic ceramic Heater is a great choice to heat a room.  Why?  well, here is what I think about my new heater.First, i was looking for a heater to use in my 160 Sq ft shop, that didn\'t take up a whole bunch of space. The Lasko heater is a good compact size, unlike Baseboard heaters that take up three to five or more feet of wall space, where you can\'t put things in front of them, this heater is only about 17" wide.  Or my former oil radiator heater, that works well, but I had to pull it out from the wall to use it, as it gets hot all around it.This heater will heat a larger room, but I chose it because I wanted a fairly fast warm up, when I start to work.  I chose Electric because I don\'t want fumes or have to worry about getting Propane, or Kerosene.  I like the feel of the Electric heat.This heater has a thermostat that can be set, and a timer if you want it to go off by itself. Very Convenient !  It draws the cool air from the floor, and blows warm air out the top, from it\'s moveable ( up and down) exhaust.  The Fan forced air can travel most of the way across the room, which helps circulate the warmth evenly.The heater fan has two speeds so it\'s quiet enough to use in a bedroom if you want, and can be put right up against the wall so it\'s out of the way.I have used this in my shop for several days now, some as cold as 25 degrees outside, and this Lasko heater warms the shop up to a comfortable (for me) 68 deg. in about 30 minutes.Because it\'s only 25" tall, the temperature the display on the front says, may need to be adjusted to your own likings, but I\'ve found once the whole room has warmed up the temp. displayed is within 2 degrees of the Thermometer I have on the other end of the room.So it does keep up with the set temperature when in thermostat mode fairly well. You can just have it on low heat or high heat all the time, but I like the convenience of the thermostat mode. It\'s simple to operate, and comes in several colors, to match your decor. While the housing is mostly Plastic, the Heater is sturdy enough. Because it is only 6.5" deep, it stays tucked up tight ot the wall out of my way, and doesn\'t heat up the wall, like my oil/electric radiator did, but fear not if you tip it over, it has automatic shutoff.I don\'t have any complaints about this heater. I think it\'s just about perfect for small shops like mine, or a cold bedroom , or even to heat larger areas. Lasko made a good all around Electric heater here.', "i've been using these for 7yrs now, after 4yrs took apart and cleaned them (i have 5) and even the 7yr old works as it did when new, i dont like to waste money so i have stuck with this model, i have the electronic version also (black)at another location, they are okay but not built the same inside, these seem to be better built, they do what they are designed to do, and i always use the ceiling fan to bring the heat down and mix it up so they dont run forever. i run 1 in each bedroom and two in the living room, not too loud, i know they are not a furnace, temperature at the grill is abt 200 degrees coming out so i use the ceiling fans on low or medium to help mix it up otherwise all the heat stays up at the ceiling. I feel this is the best heater in this class.", 'Nice heater that does a great job. Already own 6. Is an inexpensive way to heat house and safer as well. Does not impact the electric bill hardly any at all. Do not have to worry about tipping over, has solid stand. I use to use gas as a means of heating my two story house until I found this type of heater. I have purchased four or five other heaters of this type for relatives and friends.', "bought two of them in the past 2 years and both of them were defective. I have one that is 10 to 15 years old and still works. that's why i wanted one the same brand. MUST NOT BE TESTING THEM !!!", 'Unstable. No tip over feature. Never stopped outgassing plastic smell.', 'Borrowed a lasko heater last year coverage was great economical and safe so bought the same model very happy with it!', 'This heater works safely when it is sitting against the wall. To adjust to any temperature is very easy. It also shows the actual temperature in the area.', 'I purchased this heater, to use in my RV.  It is quite efficient.  Enjoying the efficiency and temperature control.  ', "I now own three (3) of 'em... The oldest one is starting its 5th winter.  ", "OUR LIVING ROOM IS BIG AND WE KEEP THE THERMOSTAT DOWN TO 68 WE NEEDED AN EXTRA HEATER TO HELP KEEP IT WARMER. WE DO NOT LIKE IT HOT TO SLEEP SO WE TRIED THIS. REALLY LIKE IT CAN STAND IT AGAINST THE WALL AND NO WORRIES. THE AIR IS DRAWN IN THE BOTTOM AND COMES OUT THE TOP NICE AND WARM.THE ONLY CHANGE I WOULD MAKE IS FOR THE AIR TO BE DRAWN IN THE TOP AND COME OUT THE BOTTOM NICE AND WARM,DUE TO COLD FLOORS. TRIED TO FIND ONE BUT DIDN'T. ANYHOW, THIS HEATER IS VERY GOOD.EASY TO MOVE. STURDY ENOUGH TO STAY STANDING.  *****    FIVE STARS"]

column1: Presto HeatDish Parabolic Electric Heater plus Footlight
column4: ['Our furnace broke and we used this heater for 5 days.  It is awesome.  It gives off lots of warm heat and we were able to make it through the Michigan 30 degree days just fine.  The light feature is great and a buzzer goes off if it is tipped over in any way! We had 3 ceramic heaters going before getting this one and The Presto HeatDish put out the heat of 3 ceramic ones!  I would highly recommend this heater especially if you are worried about safety.', "This is the only type and brand of portable heater I use anymore. It will warm your bones better than anything else on the market.  I have tried them all. If it breaks which it hasn't, I would simply go and buy another one just like it.", 'I bought this at Costco 6 years ago. We used it lightly off and on. It worked great until one day I heard a pop and it died. I searched online for tips to fix, but it seems when it dies, it dies. It did work well though. It\'s very quiet and the area it\'s pointed at gets very hot. "Low" is often enough. (Tip: put a humidifier on as well--set apart of course--and the room will get/stay toasty.) Based on reviews, I apparently got a good run out of mine. Most lasted only 3 years. While I loathe throw away products, I may have to risk buying another one if I don\'t find anything as quiet and heat producing.', "I have a very spacious living room, and this heater will heat up the entire bedroom very quickly and it is extremely quite. I really loved it. This heater doesn't take any space, it is easy to move it around anytime to anywhere. If it falls over somehow, it alerts you by noise. Very good protection. This heater Saves electricity bills too! If you set it at the temp. you would like to. The heater auto detects the room temp and shut down itself and will turn back on when the temp drops. Best heater ever used.", 'This is our 3rd parabolic heater purchased, the other 2 lasted about 10 years! Great for heating a small area, puts out a lot of heat. Hope this one lasts as long as the other two.', 'Good brand used but on very good shape', "Iam more thank pleased. I was hoping to have the heater on in the room where we sleep and by doing so cut down on the thermostat coming on as the whole room feels comfortable .I have no idea about the electric it uses sine I haven't gotten an eletric bill yet, But it has to be a lot less than the one thousand dollar bill I got for heating last month. I am very pleased thanks Richie", 'I love my presto HeatDish Plus, it heats up fast and reallywarms the space around it wonderfully. I own two now and usethem every day in the winter. Saves on gas for my furnace. Itake it with me when I drive to my childrens homes, so I am always comfortable.', 'but it still keeps you warm and i still would recommend it.', 'It will not regulate heat.  buzzer comes on and only way to stop buzzer is unplug unit from wall socket.']

New LASKO AW300 Bladeless Heatr w Remote Ctrl
column4: ['This heater is great with small children around. I recently purchased this second heater for a second room. My grandchildren were playing in the living room where one of the heaters was on. I popped into the kitchen for a second and when I returned my two year old granddaughter was playing ring a round the heater. She was putting her arm all the way through the "hole" in the middle and was not getting burned. No, I don\'t let them play with it, the point being "if" they do touch it they don\'t get burned. I believe these heaters are some of the safest on the market for that reason alone. They also perform very well! There is only one negative thing I have to say, when new, these heaters have a burning plastic smell that will make you think it is burning up and will cause you to want to return it. Before you do, put it in the garage, turn it up as hot and as high as it will go and let it run for a day or so. This will "burn" off the unpleasant burning plastic smell "before" you use it in your house or office.', 'Works great.', 'Works as described', 'Great product. Better price!', 'good product/but noisy', 'great heater works very well heats great love it i am using as bedroom heater and we have been very warm thanks']

column1: Mr Heater Buddy Portable Propane Indoor Outdoor Gas
column4: ["This heater is fairly large.  Don't expect it to fit under your legs in the bleachers.  The handle is really handy, but makes it pretty tall.This heater is very versatile. It can be like the smaller versions with just one element on at half power, full power, or both elements on full power.  It goes through propane about the same as all the other ones I've seen, and full power is a lot of power.  The fan (powered by D cells) blows warm air in your direction, which is nice because otherwise it just goes straight up.IMHO it's way handier than the smaller bottle mounted version because it doesn't tip easily and it's not as tall.  It puts the heat in a better location.It's not a small heater, but is powerful, well built, and looks like it will last.", 'this id the 2nd one I have owned  first one was 5 years old and used every day it was cold it keeps our coach warm enough on low  and very economicl to run do recomend getting the hose with regolator and using a 20 pound bbq grill tank outside  and keeping a couple of the one pound throw aways in reserve incase of a midnight run out of gas senero , teriffic for those emergencies and blizzards requires no electric to run just a couple batteries to run the fan but will still  produce  het with out fan not operating . has the o2 depletion piliot light that lifts off if o2 level gets to low plus tip switch incase it gets tipped over by accident , Like any heating device care should be taken to assure you are opperating it in a safe manner and following the instructions that states the clearences on ll sides ', 'Current house furnace is out and this unit has filled in amazingly well.  Live in MN and have 2 of these with a couple electric room heaters for 2000 sqft plus home and been heating for a month.  Do recommend the 20# Walmart propane tanks w/ gauge for $48 and conversion hose to unit for more economical heating that the small canisters.  CAn heat for nearly a week.  Have CO monitor and never have had it go off once.  They are made to be CO free .  We do not leave them running when not home for safety reason but never yet had an issue.  ', 'I bought this to be able to work in my 2 car garage during cold days. It works very well. The only drawback I could see is that the fan moves very little air. Otherwise, I would have given it a 5 star rating....  Made the garage able to be worked in with no jacket in about 2 hours (on a 15 degree day)  Well worth it...   And would be great thing to have if an ice storm hits and the power (heat) went out...  Costs less than a buck an hour worth of propane to run on High.  I bought a 15 lb tank and ran it for about 18 hours.....    I plan on getting a couple of portable 1 lb bottles and a refill adapter.....', 'Got Mr. Heater for a heater in my outside work area and as an emergency backup heater in case of power failure in a storm or the heat pump went bad in middle of winter. Works perfect and am using hooked up to 20lb propane tank and also little 1lb tanks. Either way is working perfect.  This thing will run you out of house on 18,000 btu setting.  Always vent from a window or door to keep oxygen fresh and will be good for indoor use, you will still be plenty warm and no worries about any pipes freezing. Great product', "This little heater is just the ticket for quickly warming up our home on those chilly mornings. ,I live where we seldom get any colder than 40 degrees at night , we don't run any heater at night for safety reasons ,although I feel this heater is safer than any electric one , no cords to overheat . I turn it on in the morning and in 15 minutes the chill is taken off the house. I use a small fan to circulate the heat more than the one that comes with the heater which is efficient for one room.  I also purchased the 12 foot hose and regulator so I can hook to a 30 lbs bottle out side the house. just ran the hose through an existing tv cable  hole. I can get about a week of heat out of one bottle at 16.00 to refill. That is much cheaper than running electric space heaters.", "The dogs and I have a very comfortable warm environment now that the heater is able to be used. They are so happy that the inside of the motorhome is a lot more comfortable. We have been having nights that are in the upper twenties and low 30s so we're really grateful to have a heater the prize this my cheat on low setting it it basically heats the Whole 30 ft motorhome it generates more than enough heat on low and will run for a hundred hours on that setting .  It is very warm at got my  farm in Coupeville Washington. thanks a lot for a great item!!", 'I\'ve been hunting deer for 42 years now and never worried about the cold weather when I was younger, mostly because pop-up portable blinds and portable heaters like these were not available back then. But my youngest daughter started hunting with me 6 years ago and after watching her brave a particularly cold opening day her first year I decided there had to be a better setup so she could enjoy going with me and I could insure I would get to continue to enjoy spending such moments with her, so I bought my first ground blind and my first Mr. Heater Little Buddy heater, and closing weekend of rifle season was soooooo much more enjoyable. Having a heat source to warm our feet made all the difference in the world being able to sit beside my daughter and just watch her scan our surroundings for her first deer, and did she take a beauty! After realizing how great the difference in the experience having shelter and heat made, I broke down and bought blinds for my Dad, nephew, and great friend who owns the property where we hunt, and then decided everyone should be able to stay warm and enjoy their time in the field as well, so I retired my Little Buddy heater and bought three of the Buddy heaters and one of the heater/cooker models and stocked each blind with a heater. The difference between the Little Buddy and the bigger Buddy models is very noticeably different! Running the bigger Buddy heaters warmed up a two person ground blind sufficiently enough to allow us to take off our coats, even with several windows open, and sit comfortably without creating undue noise or alerts to the deer as we watched many feed and browse around in the field in front of us. Hunting went from a cold and trying event to a greatly enjoyed experience spending time with my daughter, my Dad, my nephew, and friend! I\'ve always said a bad day hunting or fishing is better than a good day working anytime, but having Mr. Heater Buddy heaters warming our ground blinds has made such a difference in our time spent together so much more enjoyable that now my oldest daughter is joining in, and that alone made any expense paid for the equipment one of my best investments! Funny story: My Dad was using the heater I put in the blind he was using and after spending the morning hunting we all went to breakfast and I asked him how well he liked having heat, and his reply was, "great for about 20 minutes and then the damned thing quit and wouldn\'t re-light!" I asked him if he had opened any windows and he said "no, it wasn\'t light yet so I was just enjoying staying warm, until the heater went out!" I started laughing and he was taken aback by my reaction and asked why I was laughing, had I played a joke and given him the junk heater? I said no and told him he should be thankful Mr. Heater saved his life! Not knowing what I was referring to he had a puzzled look on his face, so I told him that the heater has a low oxygen sensor built into it and because he had the windows closed up fresh air could not circulate through the blind and the heater shut off before he could pass out from carbon monoxide poisoning! The look on his face was priceless! All he could say was "glad someone was looking out for him." After breakfast and getting some chores done we all went back to our blinds and my Dad made sure he opened some windows and lit the heater, and spent the rest of the day happy and warm. Moral of the story: The safety features built into Mr. Heater heaters work! Excellent design, quality built, and smart safety features all make Mr. Heater heaters great products you can trust and that make experiences during cold weather so much more enjoyable, and if having one gets a friend or family member to join in the fun, that\'s money well spent! Not to mention having the added insurance of staying warm at home should the power go out for an extended period of time during cold weather!   So, that\'s my experience with Mr. Heater heaters, and I can and do highly recommend to anyone needing and looking for a quality and dependable portable small heater, get one. You will be glad you did! ', 'Due to recently power outage frequently, I brought this protable heater for indoor use for emergency. I did not have chance to try it for hour long but I did try and find out it is very practical make and workable. Only issue to me is I don‚Äôt aware it need 4 D battery to run and how long one will last.Any how it is a very good product,I highly recommend it.', "Will be able to use it in my fish house, heat my area that I use for skinning and tanning the furs that I've trapped.  Like the fact that I can hook up to a larger propane tank.  The fan is a bonus and the 3 different heating levels are great also."]

column1: Mr Heater 30000 BTU Vent Free Blue Flame Propane Gas Wall or Floor Indoor Heater
column4: ['Great heater, literally heats my whole home, the fan could be a little more powerful but does move a little air, this was a replacement for my pellet stove, during a power outage the pellet stove would not work, with this propane Mr. heater you still have heat during an outage just no blower operation ', "The pros are the price is reasonable and no special installations is requires. I can use my RV propane tanks, so the only extras I had to buy was a regulator and connector hose.  It puts out pretty good heat, and my CO detector doesn't go off. I use it in my 24 x 30 shop.The cons are it has an odor that gets pretty strong after an hour or more.  Additionally, if I don't open a window or crack a door, within 2 hours it depletes the oxygen in the room to the point it shuts down.  The oxygen gets so low my propane torch won't fire up.  The ventilation it requires to stay running lets a lot of cold air in, offsetting the heat it produces.", "This is just what we needed.  We are in a remote area of Maine where we tend to get power failures in winter.  This unit works great and doesn't depend on electricity to keep us warm.  This is important since we can reach temps of -30 degrees F.  Highly recommend this unit.", 'We heat both houses with only ventless blue flame products, 10k, 20k and 30k units. This 30k propane unit is the best we\'ve come across. Very clean burning and as attractive a casing as they come, and a thermostat that works . Our 30k mock "cast iron stove\' unit is very attractive but not as efficient. This is our second Mr. Heater and would definitely buy from BigDealOnTheHill again if they had one.', "I bought this for a small drafty cabin I rent. hook up was easy once I ran the steel pipe from the back porch under the cabin to where I put the heater. Installed a Mr. Heater regulator on the tank end of the pipe, a Mr. Heater shut off valve and flex pipe at the heater end.I also bought and installed the optional fan for it however the it dosent turn on when you set it to auto. But constant on is ok. The temp settings seem to work fine on the heater itself though, when I put the control knob on 1, 2, 3, or 4 it shuts down and fires back up when the temp gets to those levels, I don't know what those temps actually are but on setting 5 it runs contignously.", 'This is one of the best purchases I\'ve made.  Heats very evenly with no hotspots. Wouldn\'t waste the money on the fan option. A $20 oscillating 6" fan up high works perfectly', "This is the best thing I have purchased.  It is Awesome,  the pilot light is so easy to start. The most wonderful about it is the built-in thermostat.  I turns the flame on and off. This keeps the house warm without me having to turn the heat on and off. Now with Mr. Heater my furnace hardly kicks on.  I'm Happy ", "Yes hello I've tested this product as a backup heater for my home I live in California where they threaten to shut off our power supply and I believe it will be adequate for heating my home I like it. At a constant burn it's about 1 gallon / 3 hours.", 'I\'ve had one of these heater at a remote cabin where the nighttime temperatures sometime are 23F many times during the winter.  This model does a superb job of heating the entire cabin without having to turn it up above "medium".It is easy to use and I\'ve had for ten years without any need for maintenance. I bought an extra heater for another location.  I highly recommend this unit.', "This was the cheapest solution(sale $155.00) instead of me adding a fire place. With generator, gas or wood burning stove costing significantly more. My goal was two fold, heat up my connected 2 car garage when i work on my never quite finished project car, and have heat forbmy house just in case a power outage occurs. A week after I purchased the heater. During a minus 5 degree night, my old boiler goes out at 3 am. So Mr heater is brought to my living room and the boiler contracting company says they are experiencing heavy call volume an d doesn't know when a technician will be able to Get to there but it's within 24hrs. Long story short, 3 1/2 20gallon propane tanks over 27 hours from outage to boiler being fixed. My house was kept warm and no pipes froze. So it was a worth wild investment."]

column1: Dyna-Glo Portable Forced Air Heater 60k - 125k BTU
column4: ["I won a auction for two Dyna Glo 30k-60k heaters for 75.00 shipped . Obviously by reading the description they were returned to the store for some issue and they were. The thermocouple didnt work in either one which always goes out and i always bypass anyway. They only came with one hose and regulator so i ordered another one for 8 bucks shipped. After watching a 2 minute video ( because these were different then the one i already own) it took me about 10 minutes to bypass the thermocouple on each unit and attach both hoses. I hooked both of them to a propane tank and they both worked perfectly. So i got two like new heaters for $85.00 . I read a few post before i purchased that complained about the heaters not staying lit they should have assumed they had a issue by the listing and the fact they are returns from the store. By watching a 2 minute video they couls have fixed the heater and got a great deal. A brand new thermocouple doesn't cost but 10 bucks shipped if you wanted to fix it , i prefer to bypass it . I don't like having to hold the button in for 5 minutes untill it gets hot enough to run on its on. By bypassing the thermocouple it stays lit as soon as you light it . I'm not sure how you buy a product described as returned to store and leave a bad review because it doesn't work correctly . I would have bypassed the thermocouple even if mine did work correctly but i never would have assumed it worked fine. If you looking for a brand new product work a warranty go to Lowe's arw home depot. If you have a philip head screw driver handy and you are looking for a deal like i was these work great .", 'Pretty Quiet per se. arrived Fast. Compact with good output. Your not heating a large space Quickly with this but.. it is great for maintaining the warmth after the larger space is up to temp. Using it in a 1000 Sq. Ft 14‚Äô side wall shop as 3rd Heater the 2 larger Kerosene jets get it toasty I shut them off and just run this propane Heater! Works Great even in Single digits outside in an Insulated Shop.Would buy again if needed.', 'Bought this heater to help supplement heat in our large informal office. We are presently using an 80,000 BTU kerosene heater but the fumes were bothering us when it shuts off other than that it warmed the large office space very quickly and evenly.We wanted to use the Dyna Glo because it is propane hoping there will be far less fumes. While we were attempting to get the heater to stay lit it was producing heat but not nearly as much as the kero 80K would. Nor did the fan push the heat throughout the office space as fast. This is only 20K BTU less but it felt far less than that.We had to return the Dyna-Glo. Maybe we will get another one or something a bit better and pay a few dollars more.', "It was not able to heat a one car garage on the highest setting, after about 3 hours of operating, temp. was the same inside/outside of building, could only feel the heat if standing directly 2 feet in front of it, also very loud, wouldn't recommend", 'Very good quality of product especially for the low price.', 'A very good heater  light weight  and would buy again', 'good product for the money', 'Compact /puts out lots of heat /easy set up', 'It dos the job very well !    I would buy again.', 'Work great. bought to replace a much older unit. These will heat up a small to mid size area quickley']

I repeat we have no other furnace or heater in the housethe basement stays around 60 all the time but as soon as the outdoors temps rise into the 20's and 30's it will be about 68 in here and we will only need the large Lasco heater.I am very happy with this heater.", 'Works well and looks like the picture, but not quite the remote I was looking for. column1: Mr. Heater Big Buddy Portable 18000 BTU Heater - Red
column4: ["This heater is fairly large.  Don't expect it to fit under your legs in the bleachers.  The handle is really handy, but makes it pretty tall.This heater is very versatile. It can be like the smaller versions with just one element on at half power, full power, or both elements on full power.  It goes through propane about the same as all the other ones I've seen, and full power is a lot of power.  The fan (powered by D cells) blows warm air in your direction, which is nice because otherwise it just goes straight up.IMHO it's way handier than the smaller bottle mounted version because it doesn't tip easily and it's not as tall.  It puts the heat in a better location.It's not a small heater, but is powerful, well built, and looks like it will last.", 'this id the 2nd one I have owned  first one was 5 years old and used every day it was cold it keeps our coach warm enough on low  and very economicl to run do recomend getting the hose with regolator and using a 20 pound bbq grill tank outside  and keeping a couple of the one pound throw aways in reserve incase of a midnight run out of gas senero , teriffic for those emergencies and blizzards requires no electric to run just a couple batteries to run the fan but will still  produce  het with out fan not operating . has the o2 depletion piliot light that lifts off if o2 level gets to low plus tip switch incase it gets tipped over by accident , Like any heating device care should be taken to assure you are opperating it in a safe manner and following the instructions that states the clearences on ll sides ', 'Current house furnace is out and this unit has filled in amazingly well.  Live in MN and have 2 of these with a couple electric room heaters for 2000 sqft plus home and been heating for a month.  Do recommend the 20# Walmart propane tanks w/ gauge for $48 and conversion hose to unit for more economical heating that the small canisters.  CAn heat for nearly a week.  Have CO monitor and never have had it go off once.  They are made to be CO free .  We do not leave them running when not home for safety reason but never yet had an issue.  ', 'I bought this to be able to work in my 2 car garage during cold days. It works very well. The only drawback I could see is that the fan moves very little air. Otherwise, I would have given it a 5 star rating....  Made the garage able to be worked in with no jacket in about 2 hours (on a 15 degree day)  Well worth it...   And would be great thing to have if an ice storm hits and the power (heat) went out...  Costs less than a buck an hour worth of propane to run on High.  I bought a 15 lb tank and ran it for about 18 hours.....    I plan on getting a couple of portable 1 lb bottles and a refill adapter.....', 'Got Mr. Heater for a heater in my outside work area and as an emergency backup heater in case of power failure in a storm or the heat pump went bad in middle of winter. Works perfect and am using hooked up to 20lb propane tank and also little 1lb tanks. Either way is working perfect.  This thing will run you out of house on 18,000 btu setting.  Always vent from a window or door to keep oxygen fresh and will be good for indoor use, you will still be plenty warm and no worries about any pipes freezing. Great product', "This little heater is just the ticket for quickly warming up our home on those chilly mornings. ,I live where we seldom get any colder than 40 degrees at night , we don't run any heater at night for safety reasons ,although I feel this heater is safer than any electric one , no cords to overheat . I turn it on in the morning and in 15 minutes the chill is taken off the house. I use a small fan to circulate the heat more than the one that comes with the heater which is efficient for one room.  I also purchased the 12 foot hose and regulator so I can hook to a 30 lbs bottle out side the house. just ran the hose through an existing tv cable  hole. I can get about a week of heat out of one bottle at 16.00 to refill. That is much cheaper than running electric space heaters.", "The dogs and I have a very comfortable warm environment now that the heater is able to be used. They are so happy that the inside of the motorhome is a lot more comfortable. We have been having nights that are in the upper twenties and low 30s so we're really grateful to have a heater the prize this my cheat on low setting it it basically heats the Whole 30 ft motorhome it generates more than enough heat on low and will run for a hundred hours on that setting .  It is very warm at got my  farm in Coupeville Washington. thanks a lot for a great item!!", 'I\'ve been hunting deer for 42 years now and never worried about the cold weather when I was younger, mostly because pop-up portable blinds and portable heaters like these were not available back then. But my youngest daughter started hunting with me 6 years ago and after watching her brave a particularly cold opening day her first year I decided there had to be a better setup so she could enjoy going with me and I could insure I would get to continue to enjoy spending such moments with her, so I bought my first ground blind and my first Mr. Heater Little Buddy heater, and closing weekend of rifle season was soooooo much more enjoyable. Having a heat source to warm our feet made all the difference in the world being able to sit beside my daughter and just watch her scan our surroundings for her first deer, and did she take a beauty! After realizing how great the difference in the experience having shelter and heat made, I broke down and bought blinds for my Dad, nephew, and great friend who owns the property where we hunt, and then decided everyone should be able to stay warm and enjoy their time in the field as well, so I retired my Little Buddy heater and bought three of the Buddy heaters and one of the heater/cooker models and stocked each blind with a heater. The difference between the Little Buddy and the bigger Buddy models is very noticeably different! Running the bigger Buddy heaters warmed up a two person ground blind sufficiently enough to allow us to take off our coats, even with several windows open, and sit comfortably without creating undue noise or alerts to the deer as we watched many feed and browse around in the field in front of us. Hunting went from a cold and trying event to a greatly enjoyed experience spending time with my daughter, my Dad, my nephew, and friend! I\'ve always said a bad day hunting or fishing is better than a good day working anytime, but having Mr. Heater Buddy heaters warming our ground blinds has made such a difference in our time spent together so much more enjoyable that now my oldest daughter is joining in, and that alone made any expense paid for the equipment one of my best investments! Funny story: My Dad was using the heater I put in the blind he was using and after spending the morning hunting we all went to breakfast and I asked him how well he liked having heat, and his reply was, "great for about 20 minutes and then the damned thing quit and wouldn\'t re-light!" I asked him if he had opened any windows and he said "no, it wasn\'t light yet so I was just enjoying staying warm, until the heater went out!" I started laughing and he was taken aback by my reaction and asked why I was laughing, had I played a joke and given him the junk heater? I said no and told him he should be thankful Mr. Heater saved his life! Not knowing what I was referring to he had a puzzled look on his face, so I told him that the heater has a low oxygen sensor built into it and because he had the windows closed up fresh air could not circulate through the blind and the heater shut off before he could pass out from carbon monoxide poisoning! The look on his face was priceless! All he could say was "glad someone was looking out for him." After breakfast and getting some chores done we all went back to our blinds and my Dad made sure he opened some windows and lit the heater, and spent the rest of the day happy and warm. Moral of the story: The safety features built into Mr. Heater heaters work! Excellent design, quality built, and smart safety features all make Mr. Heater heaters great products you can trust and that make experiences during cold weather so much more enjoyable, and if having one gets a friend or family member to join in the fun, that\'s money well spent! Not to mention having the added insurance of staying warm at home should the power go out for an extended period of time during cold weather!   So, that\'s my experience with Mr. Heater heaters, and I can and do highly recommend to anyone needing and looking for a quality and dependable portable small heater, get one. You will be glad you did! ', 'Due to recently power outage frequently, I brought this protable heater for indoor use for emergency. I did not have chance to try it for hour long but I did try and find out it is very practical make and workable. Only issue to me is I don‚Äôt aware it need 4 D battery to run and how long one will last.Any how it is a very good product,I highly recommend it.', "Will be able to use it in my fish house, heat my area that I use for skinning and tanning the furs that I've trapped.  Like the fact that I can hook up to a larger propane tank.  The fan is a bonus and the 3 different heating levels are great also."]

column1: Dr. Heater DR966 240-volt Hardwired Shop or Home Garage Commercial Heater
column4: ['The heater requires a 35A circuit with #8AWG wire per Article 424 of the National Electric Code. The heater only pulls 25A on highest setting, but is considered a "fixed" device with a "continuous load", so the wiring and breaker need to be rated at 125%.  That puts it at 31.25A, over a #10AWG wire and 30A breaker\'s rating.  Don\'t risk your insurance company denying your claim if something goes wrong.At that power, you don\'t want to use a line voltage thermostat designed for smaller baseboard heaters.  If you want a wall mounted thermostat, look into any conventional thermostat, a 24VAC HVAC transformer, and a 40A 2-pole 24V HVAC contactor.  I have three DR-966 heaters with their built-in thermostats all the way up and their switches on the 6000W setting, running off a single 24V transformer and Hunter 429999B thermostat, with a contactor near each heater switching the 240V AC on and off.  If I\'m not in the building I keep the thermostat at its minimum 45 degrees setting to prevent pipes from freezing.  Using a contactor, you\'re essentially automating turning the heater on and off, no different than using the instruction manual\'s method of using the circuit breaker, and not voiding any warranty.This is not an infrared heater, the manufacturer calls itself both Dr. Heater and Dr. Infrared Heater.  The heater is a wire coil type, the front two coils are 1500 watts each tied together, the rear coil is a single 3000 watt for a total of 6000 watts.  With the fan blowing on them, a spiral or two of the rear coil may get red, primarily near the coil supports.  If the fan doesn\'t turn the coil will get red hot, and probably break the support wire inside and then droop.  I received one heater that had a bent fan bracket not allowing the blade to turn and when powered up the rear coil did just that.  I received a refund to buy a third heater and since the vendor was filing a damage claim, was told to discard the defective heater if after 10 days the shipping carrier didn\'t contact me to inspect it.  After the 10 days passed without being contacted, I straightened the bracket out, verified the fan worked and then adjusted the drooping rear coil so there was a minimum of red spots.  I ended up with 3 heaters for the price of 2.Although the output of the heaters may feel like no more than a hand held hair dryer when your area is cold, follow the instruction manual\'s recommendations of keeping it the proper distances from walls and other objects.  If you feel it isn\'t putting out like it should, use a clamp-on ammeter to verify the heater is drawing around 25A on each leg with the temperature control fully clockwise and the switch on 6000W.  If it\'s not, contact the vendor.I have a 30x50 pole barn shop with a 10\' ceiling, so the roof peak is about 12\'.  It has "double bubble foil" insulation on the walls and roof, with exposed trusses.  The heater\'s manual recommends 1.25 watts of heating per cubic foot, so 30\' x 50\' x 11\' x 1.25W = 20,625 watts.  With 18,000W of heaters, I can set the thermostat at 60, go to the home store 10 miles away and by the time I get back the heaters have shut off.  If I already have my materials and I\'m in a hurry to get started, I supplement the electrics with a 3-burner 45,000 BTU tank-mounted propane heater to raise the temp to 60 faster.  So a single 6000W heater in an uninsulated 3-car garage may not be adequate.Before I contacted the eBay vendor about the damaged heater, I contacted the Dr. Heater by phone.  They told me they would send a replacement heater and pre-paid shipping label.  Then I received an email stating they would email me a label within one business day and start the replacement process.  I never received the label by email.  When I called Dr. Heater on the second business day they said they would email a label by the end of the day.  I never got that, so I resolved the issue with the eBay vendor, a 10 star solution.  So it may not be worth the stamp to send in your warranty card.  If you get a working unit, it\'s worth the money.  Good luck repairing one later, since parts don\'t seem to be available.  Due to one of mine having a bent fan bracket, if you get a DR-966 in the 160014xx serial number range, stick a screwdriver in the back and try to spin the fan blade before installation.  A pallet of these might have gotten dropped on the dock after coming off a ship from China.  If that bracket was bent before the heater was assembled, then don\'t trust the QC sticker on the back. It hasn\'t got to zero outside yet, and I haven\'t got my first electric bill, so I may be in for a shock in that respect.', "It's an OK heater. You MUST user the heavy 8 gauge wire and the 35 amp circuit breakers that the instructions say. It has a much quieter fan than my old one, so that's a really nice thing. Puts out a good amount of heat for a small heater. So Great so far? The only bad thing that I have to say about it, is the same as a couple other reviews. The thermostat just doesn't work right. It turns on at 65 degrees and cycles on and off like you would expect. But during the day it keeps turning on more and more warming up the shop by turning on at higher and higher temps. By the end of the day it was turning on at 79 degrees and this was with the thermostat not being moved, set the same all day long. So if it had a better thermostat it would easily be a 5 Star heater. Better yet a remote mounted thermostat would be Great! Heats up my well insulated shop 20X16X8 even when it dropped to zero outside. So it's a GREAT heater with a crappy thermostat.         ", 'Installed this heater on a 20 degree day in a dairy milk house ( block building). It had that space up 65 degrees in 20 minutes.This was at the full 6000 watts. Then left the thermostat at 3/4. This was adequate for me. Maybe 70 degrees at full power? A really quality unit for price!', '1000 square foot shop stays warm when it‚Äôs 30 degrees outside. I keep the temp about 58 to 60 when working. Any warmer and it‚Äôs not comfortable. Fairly quite on high.  Great value on a heater. Propane was costly and dangerous in a shop using flammable liquids. ', 'I got this as an open box, but looks brand new.  Got it for a great price.  I have it on a 30 amp breaker with #10 wire.  Seems to work very well with no issues.', 'Nice heater for its size...Puts out a fair amount of heat.Will probably consume a fair amount of electricity if my calculations are right', "This is a well built product at a reasonable price. It is easy to install. It cycles properly and maintains the temperature in my 24'X24' garage. I was expecting more fan noise but it is fairly  quiet.", 'Its a good product for the money', 'Does a good job heating my garage/wood shop.Some mentioned a need to upgrade the electrical capacity. I have a 30 amp breaker with #10 gauge wire. Recommendations are 8 gauge with a 35 amp breaker.I decided to check the amp load of the heater before upgrading. I wired it up and put my clamp meter on both legs at high power. Reading was 21-22 amps per leg. 10 gauge wire is rated for 30 amps. I now run the heater on low when not present in the shop. I switch to high only when I‚Äôm in the shop if necessary.No problems at all. Puts out the heat when I need it.Anyway, I do plan on upgrading wiring and breaker when the weather warms up.Good heater, good price.', "Heater  works great. Its keeping my shop comfortably warm without busting hot air on you like some other heaters I've used."]
