column1: DuraHeat Propane (LP) 360 Tank Top Heater
column4: ['This heater works wonderfully.  Love it.  Could not get it to start at first set on low but starts very easily when set on medium.  Puts out good lateral heat, so it works well to gather around it,   Other heaters I considered, most of the heat goes strait up into the air.  ', "Just got this and tried it twice this afternoon. I do not have the nerve to try it again. It assembles to the tank easily. Lights easily and burns for about three minutes on low just perfectly. Then you hear a small roaring sound that last for another 60 seconds, the BAM. Sounds like a small explosion. I think I might sit it out in the middle of my back yard and see what happens if I don't jump to shut it down immediately like I did twice today. Looks like a Chinese bomb to me. ", "Mount is not strong.  It works but I think more heat goes up in warm air than is radiated.  Heaters with metal radiators don't work as well as ones with ceramic elements.", 'The best type of heater for your patio or deck. 360 degree heat area. Low setting is always plenty. Parts are easy to find. ', "Love it!  We have quite a few propane tanks hanging around, so all we needed to do was get this and put it on top.  Heats up quickly.  We hang out outside and use this to keep warm.  We have the tall propane heater as well, but this one is lower and heats your midsection.  At this price, it's a great bargain!", "Works great. The only thing is I couldn't light it through the hole and just directly on the burner works well.", 'This space heater does the job I need it to do.  Heat output is very adequate.  3 heat settings on an easy to read dial.  Assembly was easy.  Attaching it to the tank was easy.  Heat output is straight up in a fairly narrow column, so I made a metal spreader that sits on top to widen the heat plume.', 'TT-360 Duraheat works awesome, easy light (match), 3 settings and plenty of heat for my work area. column1: Hiland-HLDS01-CGT-Tall Patio Heater Hammered Bronze Finish
column4: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won‚Äôt light. Very disappointing! I‚Äôm going to see if I can get it serviced since I‚Äôm desperate to have a gas heater for outdoor use for my business.  If I can‚Äôt get it to light, I‚Äôm returning it.', "I purchased it couple of years ago, but after couple of time using it, the heater wouldn't turn on!!! I only used it twice the first year, and it still looks nice but it doesn't work. I didn't realized that I had purchased the 3 year insurance online for it, so when I realized that I have insurance, I filed a claim to get it serviced or replaced, but insurance company was not very helpful, and asked to have it repaired at a certified repair shop, which I didn't find one in OC county, and the other option was to give 50% of the cost!! I rather they would sent a repairman to fix it or replace it!!", 'This was easy to set up and works great! We had one minor issue and that was the latch for the door. It didn‚Äôt come with the bolts for that but no problem a couple small nuts and bolts from my garage and it is awesome!', 'The Items are both working fine so far. My only issue is, one of the items was considerably damaged as you can see in the pictures.', 'Incredible bargain, and very well made. Hot! Hot! Hot1 The assembly is a bit challenging, but worth the effort.', 'As described, very well made, nice looking!', 'Great price.  Works as advertised.  would recommend']

column1: Broan 174 10.5A 1500W 120 to 240V Steel White Fan-Forced Wall Heater 9-1/4 H in.
column4: ['We bought two heaters by different manufacturers in order to compare. This one is quieter and heats better. The thermostat works better and is more accurate. Great unit, it keeps a 230 square foot room warm even in 10 degree F weather.', 'I bought this heater to replace the same one I installed in my lower level bathroom 20 years ago. The replacement was exactly the same size which made the replacement of the internal parts in the existing sheet metal frame very fast. It works well for this small bath to take the chill of the lower level out between heating seasons. After removing the existing Broan 174 I saw a build up of lint/dust on the back side of the heater eliment and it may not have been bad to begin with, so I will keep that in mind if it starts smelling hot (In the next 20 years). Bottom line is it work well to heat a small room quickly.', 'Very good to use in a small bathroom,I run it 240v for less power consumption ', 'it was exactly what I wanted --keeps my small bathroom very warm', 'Easy to install, heat is fast, fan is quiet, looks great.', 'This is the 5th of these heaters I have purchased. column1: Bladeless Heatr w Remote Ctrl
column4: ['This heater is great with small children around. I recently purchased this second heater for a second room. My grandchildren were playing in the living room where one of the heaters was on. I popped into the kitchen for a second and when I returned my two year old granddaughter was playing ring a round the heater. She was putting her arm all the way through the "hole" in the middle and was not getting burned. No, I don\'t let them play with it, the point being "if" they do touch it they don\'t get burned. I believe these heaters are some of the safest on the market for that reason alone. They also perform very well! There is only one negative thing I have to say, when new, these heaters have a burning plastic smell that will make you think it is burning up and will cause you to want to return it. Before you do, put it in the garage, turn it up as hot and as high as it will go and let it run for a day or so. This will "burn" off the unpleasant burning plastic smell "before" you use it in your house or office.', 'Works great.', 'Works as described', 'Great product. column1: DuraHeat Propane (LP) 360 Tank Top Heater
column4: ['This heater works wonderfully.  Love it.  Could not get it to start at first set on low but starts very easily when set on medium.  Puts out good lateral heat, so it works well to gather around it,   Other heaters I considered, most of the heat goes strait up into the air.  ', "Just got this and tried it twice this afternoon. I do not have the nerve to try it again. It assembles to the tank easily. Lights easily and burns for about three minutes on low just perfectly. Then you hear a small roaring sound that last for another 60 seconds, the BAM. Sounds like a small explosion. I think I might sit it out in the middle of my back yard and see what happens if I don't jump to shut it down immediately like I did twice today. Looks like a Chinese bomb to me. ", "Mount is not strong.  It works but I think more heat goes up in warm air than is radiated.  Heaters with metal radiators don't work as well as ones with ceramic elements.", 'The best type of heater for your patio or deck. 360 degree heat area. Low setting is always plenty. Parts are easy to find. ', "Love it!  We have quite a few propane tanks hanging around, so all we needed to do was get this and put it on top.  Heats up quickly.  We hang out outside and use this to keep warm.  We have the tall propane heater as well, but this one is lower and heats your midsection.  At this price, it's a great bargain!", "Works great. column4: ["this little heater will heat your small room to a toasty comfort level in just minutes, with the remote control everything is a snap and no need to get out of your seat, it is that easy to use, it's compact so it fits anywhere in a room giving you space, this product was a really good price,", "I love this heater. No more freezing with a little space heater.", 'I recommend knowledg√§ble HVAC guy to add the external thermostat if you need one.  I have high ceilings and wanted to use my mouting system that √¢ttaches to the walls in a corner - no ceiling holes, but two nights of engineering the aluminum mounts. Obviously this is meant to be used in a smaller, more insulated setting.  I wanted to try just one first, and then add as necessary.The heater itself seems to be well-built as far as structure, and designed well as far as installation and operation.  Including running wiring and building a wall mount (vaulted ceiling so no ceiling studs), it took 2-3hrs to get up and running.In my large uninsulated setting, over the course of 3-4hrs, it was able to raise the temperature from 25*F to 45*F, roughly speaking.  In other words, from intolerable to tolerable.  Which is about what I expected from it.  I think it would do quite well at maintaining a higher temperature if I were to use my propane 'salamander' to initially heat the space.Based on other's reviews and my own experience, there seems to be a major quality control concern in the assembly line for these regarding the fan nut.  I was unaware of this until after it was installed, but I'm almost certain I have the same issue as almost everyone else.  Before mounting the heater there was a nut and washer rattling around inside.  After a semi-thorough check, I figured it was an erroneous leftover.  Having read the reviews and after hearing a small rattle when the heater runs, I will be dismounting and tearing it down to install that nut properly.  This is both an inconvenience and really a potential danger.  For that I've removed a star from the rating.That being said, I will be purchasing another one, possibly two more.  Can't beat the price to performance ratio anywhere.Edit from the future:  I bought another one, slightly updated since the first.  This one had no problems and even runs quieter.  Awesome.", "This heater does a great job heating my 24'x30' insulated shop. I have it on a Honeywell line thermostat, and typically keep it at 40* to keep water lines from freezing, but when I'm ready to work in the ship I just turn it up and in 20 minutes it's nice and toasty. The other day it was 30* outside, but on high this ran for less than 5 minutes every 20-30 minutes.The only potential negative to be aware of is that it has a slight whistle when it's running. It's enough that I think about it every time it starts up, but it's not enough to be a nuisance.Overall I'm very happy with my purchase; it was easy to install, and is cost-effective for the job I needed it to do.", "Fast shipping.Well packaged.All metal construction.Enough detail in instructions,easily installed,best of all:heater works great.No issues so far.I heat a decent size 2 car garage and this is all I need.Recomend a ceiling fan to force the heat down,same thing with all of 'em.I can not stand beneath this heater when it is on high,it is way beyond my expectations.It is not very big or impressive,but do not let that part fool ya,it is a good heater.I have left the thermostat inside the heater,so far this is working fine.", 'I have used 4 times now and I really like it. If you have a insulated two car garage this heater will do the job nicely.It only took about 30 minutes to go from 30¬∞ to  62¬∞ in an hour it was 71¬∞ had to turn it down to work though. I like it 57¬∞ to 63¬∞ when working on a project. This heater is perfect for my needs. Little less than $100 too!üëç', "I'm happy with this heater and wish I'd found it years ago. I installed it in my basement workshop and it is way better than the big baseboard heater and kerosene heater I'd been using for many years. It's quiet and easy to install and heats the basement better than I'd anticipated. The workmanship and quality are great and I especially like that the sheet metal parts are post painted as opposed to crummy pre-paint and so all the sheet metal cut edges and corners are painted and nice and smooth and burr free.", 'I use this heater turned down low just to knock the edge off the cold so I can work comfortably in my 3 car garage shop.  I have it set on about 1/3 of its capacity and it keeps the garage at about 55- 60, the way I like it.  If I were to turn it up on high it would make the garage toasty warm.  The installation was straight forward and simple.  I bought a plug, 15 ft. of 10-3 service cord and a cord grip to make the installation. I plug it into my 220 volt welder receptacle when I want to have heat.  Wish I had found it years ago.', 'Great heat output, replaced my floor oil heater and small plug in with this one.  Only reason I gave it a 4 not 5 is that # 1 the fan blade was loose when I got it and the simple mechanism makes a rattling noise that is not necessary.  It only has a moving fan part but is kinda noisy.  Heats very well.']

column1: EUH4000 Electric Workspace Heater, 3750-Watts - Quantity 1
column4: ["What works ? It puts out heat ! What doesn't work is the fact that it does not (cycle) on & off like a heater should ...... IT runs all the time and i mean all the time ! By that i mean you are able to turn down the temperature but that's it ! it runs constantly and does not shut off unless you physically turn the switch off ....... My other heater once the garage reached the set temp it would automatically shut off until it needed to come back on again and so on all thru the nite thus saving me money on the electric bill because the temp stayed current ! That being said once i get my other heater repaired I will be putting it back in service and the (dura heat) I will put it away.For this feature alone not cycling on & off is why i gave it only 3-stars.", 'Hope it will be safe to use in my house! I went  through last winter with 2 small box type electric heaters and had to wear a coat in the house part of the time. Hoping this heater will. take the chill off so my smaller ones can keep up!', 'Good unit, seems to be built of good quality. The thermostat does not shut off the fan, only the heat tube.I was looking for something that would shut off completely when the set temp is obtained.', 'My workshop is just a little over 600 sq. feet and this thing heats it up quickly. Make sure you understand that it runs off 220 and not 100!', 'Dura heat 4000 watt hanging heater is well designed, well finished, and easily placed from wall or ceiling.  Resistive electric heat is clean, convenient, economical, and if necessary can be replaced for less cost than a service visit.', 'The only thing i do not like about it is the fan runs all the time it is on, dose not cut off with thermostat turn off.', 'fan never shuts off', 'Great heater !!']

column1: Comfort Zone Digital Fan-Forced Ceiling Mount Heater + Remote and LCD Display
column4: ["This replaced a 40 y/o unit that worked, but not well. Having the remote control makes temperature control much easier. The high mode provides instant heat when used and the guide vanes direct the flow well. I did replace the circuit breaker as this unit has a max draw of 31.4 amps (7500 watts)on high mode, and insured the wiring and connections were proper. It's below freezing outside and this unit cycles and maintains 63-68 degrees with a 72 degree setting. The area is an insulated 900 sqft and the temperature is read on the wall furthest from the unit. Until I get a better primary heat source this is a great unit to have till then.", "The heater is built pretty tough, which is a good thing. I also found it easy to connect, which interestingly enough was more expensive for the materials than it was for the heater. Only problem is that it doesn't heat as well as advertised. It claimed to heat an area (uninsulated) that was 30x30. my garage is 25x35 so I figured that was basically the same thing. after running for an hour or more it only brought the temp up from 45* to about 52*. I guess that if I left it running all the time it would eventually gey there, but that was not what I was hoping for. Plus, those temps were only for the emediate area around the heater, the far end of the garage was still ice cold. In any account it is a good heater for the price. especially if you already have a place wired for it.", "Havent used it yet, but looks nice. It's smaller than I thought but as long as it heats good then I'm ok with it. I was a little disappointed that it didnt come with the plug. Luckily I have an extra one. I will have it hooked up in a couple of days. Thanks. ", "Installed in my 2 car garage, used the correct 8ga wire and double pole breaker. On high setting, it trips the breaker. Tried a different breaker, no luck. It doesn't heat the garage as well as I anticipated, but better than having no heater at all. I like the remote, it works well. Heater is quiet. Not impressed but whatever. I may end up moving it to my basement, where I believe it may work better. ", 'After researching different heater I found this to be the best deal, but the heat sensor is on the inside witch makes it shut off sooner than it should so I located it on the outside and it now works good. I also looked on youtube to see how to hook up 220w and found it to be really easy but make sure you use 8/3 wire and a 40amp double pull breaker for safety reasons. I have a 24x30 insulated garage with 8 foot ceilings and at 32 degrees it will heat up at about 10 degrees an hour and after a while when the heat is up a little bit it seems to heat up faster so I use my kerosene heater to speed things up a little and when it gets around 68 degrees this heater can maintain very easy. now just so you know I have 4 metal cars in my garage that retain cold air for quite a while so your garage might heat up faster depending what you have in it', "I purchased this unit to replace my old one. The unit arrived very quickly. I think it took 4 days to get to me. Packaging was very stout, no damage to the unit. I did have a friend of mine help me install it but it wasn't really hard and could have done it in a pinch. Instructions were easy to read. I have a 25x25 sq ft shop, insulated to about R4 and this heater does a nice job of warming it with outside temps around around 32F. This unit is also nice in that I have a choice of hi or lo elements used to heat.I would recommend this and install it myself if I go to a larger building.", 'Great price, great size, easy to use', "Not happy with this heater. First of all, the thermostat is not correct, as it is located INSIDE the heater where it stays hot. Must be set much much higher for desired temp. Second, and worst of all, when the heater switches ON or OFF, it makes a extremely loud BANG. Really disappointing for the price and would return it if it wasn't hard wired in. Regret buying the warranty, as I don't plan on keeping past it's first breakdown.", 'The temperature sensor is mounted in a way that the heater cuts off way before room temperature is reached.  Believe the sensor is getting reading from the case rather than ambient temperature.  ', 'Well Made. Easy to use. Shipping was fast, with damage. Easy to install. Easy to hang. Would highly recommend it if the square footage is right and it is insulated.']

column1: Dr Infrared Heater Portable Space Heater 1500-Watt
column4: ["Pros-outside of unit not hot if you touch it.it's on wheels, cycles on to adjust set temperature, has a remote, has a timer, safety switches ( temp & if it tips over ). Youtube videos on how to repair unit, parts available. Looks nice, immediate heat, does not deplete oxygen like a ceramic heater, you can breath easily.Cons- 1500 watts & 12.5 amps power used. Monitor it when you first use it, a weak or bad electrical receptacle can arc! Your plug or power cord could melt or burn. The risk always exists when you use it. I use to do electrician work long ago, be mindful.Read all instructions thoroughly and completely! DO NOT LEAVE UNATTENDED! I still like to use this heater, in fact I own two of them. Follow all safety warnings, it can be a good heater, don't let your guard down.....be vigilant, be safe, and stay warm. I watch TV with one keeping me warm, and happy.", "Impressed with quality and many features like holding heat level economically, auto dual fan speeds, easy reading temperature, easy set up and great looking unit. Doesn't even look like a heater, more like a piece of furniture or a speaker for a high end stereo system.", 'I hen purchase several brands of infrared heaters .   Dr. Heater is built solid .  Purchased my last one in 2013.   Warranty is unsurpassed with 3 years .  Most heaters just won‚Äôt last .  Also puts our more heat output than a comparable EdenPure .   Good value and great  quality .', 'It is a hybrid infrared.  60% of the heat comes from a relatively new PTC heater.  40% comes from infrared.  It heats the air and objects in the room at the same time.  I have a small home of 1250 sq. ft.  I have three of these heaters at various places and have been able to shut my gas furnace down entirely.  Since they are very stingy on electricity, my monthly heating bill is now much less than it used to be!  I would recommend this heater to anyone without hesitation!', 'My Dr 968 1500 watt heater produces heat rapidly and cycles on and off to keep the temp where it is set.  This small unit has a fan that is barely audible and manages to push the heat away from the heat elements into the room and keep the area comfortable.  Lots of heat in a small package.', 'Well-built unit. Small, unobtrusive, and quiet. Easy to use with control panel or remote control, and the built-in thermostat works as it should. A nice feature is that the unit is on wheels so makes it easy to roll out of the way when cleaning and vacuuming. Takes the chill off my small place quite nicely. Great to use during those in-between seasons before or after you shut down or turn on the heating system. I am very satisfied with this product!', 'I have read a great deal of reviews from others before my first purchase. I have other brand spot heaters in my collection. Trial by error I suppose. Colorado Winters can be brutal at times. I purchased this for my mothers not well insulated home. a living room and a kitchen connected, 630 sq ft. this heater will keep it at a comfortable temp. for her. All at a low setting.Shuts off as it should to measure the heat in the room and comes back on when it needs to.It is supplemental. It will not heat a whole home.My unit arrived with a cracked frame on the top left corner. It works though, that is my main concern.Stays on five hours as i programmed and shuts off. Good Bang for the Buck. 5200 BTU is a great output for this size The fan is quiet when running. You can watch t.v. without noticing the heater on.In my opinion, if these units are used wisely, they are useful and can save a bit of money on your bill. Thumbs up on this unit.........', "I bought this to use in a bedroom because it was advertised as quiet, and it came with a remote.  It's not that quiet- just a little quieter than your average cheapo space heater.  And the remote doesn't power the heater on or off- just lets the unit go on standby, which is kind of a drag.  The standby light is so bright i wound up covering it with a piece of paper.  Except for the remote, it's not worth the money.", 'Despite the fact that the first heater stopped working after 4 years I purchased another, Reasons: great features, heats area very well, low cost to operate, compact and easy to move around', "Product arrived extremely quickly.  I'm using it in a sun-room to keep the temperatures steady for two parrots.  Am not able to determine if I am saving money on this product or not running it continuously versus other types of heating methods.  Product works well - happy so far."]

column1: Dr Infrared Heater Portable Space Heater 1500-Watt
column4: ["Pros-outside of unit not hot if you touch it.it's on wheels, cycles on to adjust set temperature, has a remote, has a timer, safety switches ( temp & if it tips over ). Youtube videos on how to repair unit, parts available. Looks nice, immediate heat, does not deplete oxygen like a ceramic heater, you can breath easily.Cons- 1500 watts & 12.5 amps power used. Monitor it when you first use it, a weak or bad electrical receptacle can arc! Your plug or power cord could melt or burn. The risk always exists when you use it. I use to do electrician work long ago, be mindful.Read all instructions thoroughly and completely! DO NOT LEAVE UNATTENDED! I still like to use this heater, in fact I own two of them. Follow all safety warnings, it can be a good heater, don't let your guard down.....be vigilant, be safe, and stay warm. I watch TV with one keeping me warm, and happy.", "Impressed with quality and many features like holding heat level economically, auto dual fan speeds, easy reading temperature, easy set up and great looking unit. Doesn't even look like a heater, more like a piece of furniture or a speaker for a high end stereo system.", 'I hen purchase several brands of infrared heaters .   Dr. Heater is built solid .  Purchased my last one in 2013.   Warranty is unsurpassed with 3 years .  Most heaters just won‚Äôt last .  Also puts our more heat output than a comparable EdenPure .   Good value and great  quality .', 'It is a hybrid infrared.  60% of the heat comes from a relatively new PTC heater.  40% comes from infrared.  It heats the air and objects in the room at the same time.  I have a small home of 1250 sq. ft.  I have three of these heaters at various places and have been able to shut my gas furnace down entirely.  Since they are very stingy on electricity, my monthly heating bill is now much less than it used to be!  I would recommend this heater to anyone without hesitation!', 'My Dr 968 1500 watt heater produces heat rapidly and cycles on and off to keep the temp where it is set.  This small unit has a fan that is barely audible and manages to push the heat away from the heat elements into the room and keep the area comfortable.  Lots of heat in a small package.', 'Well-built unit. Small, unobtrusive, and quiet. Easy to use with control panel or remote control, and the built-in thermostat works as it should. A nice feature is that the unit is on wheels so makes it easy to roll out of the way when cleaning and vacuuming. Takes the chill off my small place quite nicely. Great to use during those in-between seasons before or after you shut down or turn on the heating system. I am very satisfied with this product!', 'I have read a great deal of reviews from others before my first purchase. I have other brand spot heaters in my collection. Trial by error I suppose. Colorado Winters can be brutal at times. I purchased this for my mothers not well insulated home. a living room and a kitchen connected, 630 sq ft. this heater will keep it at a comfortable temp. for her. All at a low setting.Shuts off as it should to measure the heat in the room and comes back on when it needs to.It is supplemental. It will not heat a whole home.My unit arrived with a cracked frame on the top left corner. It works though, that is my main concern.Stays on five hours as i programmed and shuts off. Good Bang for the Buck. 5200 BTU is a great output for this size The fan is quiet when running. You can watch t.v. without noticing the heater on.In my opinion, if these units are used wisely, they are useful and can save a bit of money on your bill. Thumbs up on this unit.........', "I bought this to use in a bedroom because it was advertised as quiet, and it came with a remote.  It's not that quiet- just a little quieter than your average cheapo space heater.  And the remote doesn't power the heater on or off- just lets the unit go on standby, which is kind of a drag.  The standby light is so bright i wound up covering it with a piece of paper.  Except for the remote, it's not worth the money.", 'Despite the fact that the first heater stopped working after 4 years I purchased another, Reasons: great features, heats area very well, low cost to operate, compact and easy to move around', "Product arrived extremely quickly.  I'm using it in a sun-room to keep the temperatures steady for two parrots.  Am not able to determine if I am saving money on this product or not running it continuously versus other types of heating methods.  Product works well - happy so far."]

column1: Stiebel Eltron Heater 120 Volts 1500 Watts Surface Mount Quiet Operation 074058
column4: ['When I bought my business, the 4 restrooms were heated only with surface mounted electric heaters. It seemed like I was replacing one at least every 2 years. They were poorly made, noisy, and had to be run with a separate thermostat that also was prone to fail.Then I bought the Stiebel Eltron. It is quiet, attractive looking, works GREAT, and has the thermostat built in. The quality is outstanding. I plan on replacing all of them with these. (And for comparison the cost is only slightly higher.)', 'Very simple to install and provides fairly even heat in a small room or additional heat in areas that need it when extremely cold outside . This is the second unit I bought and would not hesitate to purchase again .', 'Worked well, from the reviews I was expecting better than ones at 1/2 the price.   If the fan produced more volume it might have made the difference.  ', 'Looks great mounted on wall in my studio. Easy to hook up.', 'The best love it.', 'This is not a large heater, but it is just right for my needs.It will heat one small bedroom or bath with ease.Theromostat works great on this unit.Easy to install.This unit is has a sound level, I would say is very low.', "Exactly as described. column1: Hiland-HLDS01-CGT-Tall Patio Heater Hammered Bronze Finish
column4: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won‚Äôt light. Very disappointing! I‚Äôm going to see if I can get it serviced since I‚Äôm desperate to have a gas heater for outdoor use for my business.  If I can‚Äôt get it to light, I‚Äôm returning it.', "I purchased it couple of years ago, but after couple of time using it, the heater wouldn't turn on!!! I only used it twice the first year, and it still looks nice but it doesn't work. I didn't realized that I had purchased the 3 year insurance online for it, so when I realized that I have insurance, I filed a claim to get it serviced or replaced, but insurance company was not very helpful, and asked to have it repaired at a certified repair shop, which I didn't find one in OC county, and the other option was to give 50% of the cost!! I rather they would sent a repairman to fix it or replace it!!", 'This was easy to set up and works great! We had one minor issue and that was the latch for the door. It didn‚Äôt come with the bolts for that but no problem a couple small nuts and bolts from my garage and it is awesome!', 'The Items are both working fine so far. My only issue is, one of the items was considerably damaged as you can see in the pictures.', 'Incredible bargain, and very well made. Hot! Hot! Hot1 The assembly is a bit challenging, but worth the effort.', 'As described, very well made, nice looking!', 'Great price.  Works as advertised.  would recommend']

column1: Hiland-HLDS01-CGT-Tall Patio Heater Hammered Bronze Finish
column4: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won‚Äôt light. Very disappointing! I‚Äôm going to see if I can get it serviced since I‚Äôm desperate to have a gas heater for outdoor use for my business.  If I can‚Äôt get it to light, I‚Äôm returning it.', "I purchased it couple of years ago, but after couple of time using it, the heater wouldn't turn on!!! I only used it twice the first year, and it still looks nice but it doesn't work. I didn't realized that I had purchased the 3 year insurance online for it, so when I realized that I have insurance, I filed a claim to get it serviced or replaced, but insurance company was not very helpful, and asked to have it repaired at a certified repair shop, which I didn't find one in OC county, and the other option was to give 50% of the cost!! I rather they would sent a repairman to fix it or replace it!!", 'This was easy to set up and works great! We had one minor issue and that was the latch for the door. It didn‚Äôt come with the bolts for that but no problem a couple small nuts and bolts from my garage and it is awesome!', 'The Items are both working fine so far. My only issue is, one of the items was considerably damaged as you can see in the pictures.', 'Incredible bargain, and very well made. Hot! Hot! Hot1 The assembly is a bit challenging, but worth the effort.', 'As described, very well made, nice looking!', 'Great price.  Works as advertised.  would recommend']

column1: Decorative Electric Cabinet Space Heater w/Remote &Timer ~ 1500W ~ Portable
column4: ["Pros-outside of unit not hot if you touch it.it's on wheels, cycles on to adjust set temperature, has a remote, has a timer, safety switches ( temp & if it tips over ). Youtube videos on how to repair unit, parts available. Looks nice, immediate heat, does not deplete oxygen like a ceramic heater, you can breath easily.Cons- 1500 watts & 12.5 amps power used. Monitor it when you first use it, a weak or bad electrical receptacle can arc! Your plug or power cord could melt or burn. The risk always exists when you use it. I use to do electrician work long ago, be mindful.Read all instructions thoroughly and completely! DO NOT LEAVE UNATTENDED! I still like to use this heater, in fact I own two of them. Follow all safety warnings, it can be a good heater, don't let your guard down.....be vigilant, be safe, and stay warm. I watch TV with one keeping me warm, and happy.", "Impressed with quality and many features like holding heat level economically, auto dual fan speeds, easy reading temperature, easy set up and great looking unit. Doesn't even look like a heater, more like a piece of furniture or a speaker for a high end stereo system.", 'I hen purchase several brands of infrared heaters .   Dr. Heater is built solid .  Purchased my last one in 2013.   Warranty is unsurpassed with 3 years .  Most heaters just won‚Äôt last .  Also puts our more heat output than a comparable EdenPure .   Good value and great  quality .', 'It is a hybrid infrared.  60% of the heat comes from a relatively new PTC heater.  40% comes from infrared.  It heats the air and objects in the room at the same time.  I have a small home of 1250 sq. ft.  I have three of these heaters at various places and have been able to shut my gas furnace down entirely.  Since they are very stingy on electricity, my monthly heating bill is now much less than it used to be!  I would recommend this heater to anyone without hesitation!', 'My Dr 968 1500 watt heater produces heat rapidly and cycles on and off to keep the temp where it is set.  This small unit has a fan that is barely audible and manages to push the heat away from the heat elements into the room and keep the area comfortable.  Lots of heat in a small package.', 'Well-built unit. Small, unobtrusive, and quiet. Easy to use with control panel or remote control, and the built-in thermostat works as it should. A nice feature is that the unit is on wheels so makes it easy to roll out of the way when cleaning and vacuuming. Takes the chill off my small place quite nicely. Great to use during those in-between seasons before or after you shut down or turn on the heating system. I am very satisfied with this product!', 'I have read a great deal of reviews from others before my first purchase. I have other brand spot heaters in my collection. Trial by error I suppose. Colorado Winters can be brutal at times. I purchased this for my mothers not well insulated home. a living room and a kitchen connected, 630 sq ft. this heater will keep it at a comfortable temp. for her. All at a low setting.Shuts off as it should to measure the heat in the room and comes back on when it needs to.It is supplemental. It will not heat a whole home.My unit arrived with a cracked frame on the top left corner. It works though, that is my main concern.Stays on five hours as i programmed and shuts off. Good Bang for the Buck. 5200 BTU is a great output for this size The fan is quiet when running. You can watch t.v. without noticing the heater on.In my opinion, if these units are used wisely, they are useful and can save a bit of money on your bill. Thumbs up on this unit.........', "I bought this to use in a bedroom because it was advertised as quiet, and it came with a remote.  It's not that quiet- just a little quieter than your average cheapo space heater.  And the remote doesn't power the heater on or off- just lets the unit go on standby, which is kind of a drag.  The standby light is so bright i wound up covering it with a piece of paper.  Except for the remote, it's not worth the money.", 'Despite the fact that the first heater stopped working after 4 years I purchased another, Reasons: great features, heats area very well, low cost to operate, compact and easy to move around', "Product arrived extremely quickly.  I'm using it in a sun-room to keep the temperatures steady for two parrots.  Am not able to determine if I am saving money on this product or not running it continuously versus other types of heating methods.  Product works well - happy so far."]

column1: Cadet Fan Forced In-Wall Electric Heater 2,000-Watt 240 Volt White
column4: ["It was replacing an aged wall heater that had finally given up the ghost. It was a 1500 watt model, but after installing the Com-Pak, that was only 1000 watts, it's output was higher. And it's construction was obviously of high higher quality.  And it is much quieter than old was, even when it was new. Only problem I had was it was slightly smaller to fit into the original hole in the wall.  Not the fault of the heater. I'm a bit of a handy-man so just shimmed the hole and trimmed it with some molding and it looks pretty good.", 'I have been dealing with electrical items and electricity for 60 years, andthis heater beats any I have ever dealt with. To be as small as it is, easy to mount,,but the most important thing is 2000 watts and only pulling 8.3 amps seems unreal. Most electric heaters 120 v, 1500 watts pull 12...I have just ordered another one and plan on another. I've had two of these in the past, and they have always worked well.", "We have a small house in s.e. mich.. about 700 sq. ft. on the main level.  several years ago our furnace quit and we've been using ceramic heaters ever since.  I bought this lasco heater this fall to see if it could do better than the previous heater and it has been keeping the wholehouseat about 66 to 68 degrees so far.  Right now we are having the coldest below zero weather in years and it is still keeping things at around 60 with no other heater. needless to say, we have turned on an additional ceramic heater and the temp in the living room isaround 65. I repeat we have no other furnace or heater in the housethe basement stays around 60 all the time but as soon as the outdoors temps rise into the 20's and 30's it will be about 68 in here and we will only need the large Lasco heater.I am very happy with this heater.", 'Works well and looks like the picture, but not quite the remote I was looking for.  I understand the remote that actually went with my upright fan, the model is now out of date or for sale.', 'I plugged the space heaters in immediately and it took the chill right off the house love them. I have a heat pump and when the temperature gets below 32 the system needs help. These are perfect.', 'Quiet; Very powerful; Many fan & heat speed/temperature options. Delivered much faster than even my dog\'s favorite (E-bay) dog food! The back of this unit is not even the slightest bit warm, even when temperature and fan speed are at "max"! Greatly helps supplement our home\'s central heat, even during extremely cold weather.', "This heater warms my apartment way better than the heating sytem for the apartment. column1: World Marketing Of America Electric Workspace Heater, 4800-Watts
column4: ['This heater throws s lot of heat. I like that the fan stays on so it cools down when element shuts off. I plan to install a 220 volt ac led indicator light so I can see when element is on so I can adjust the thermostat.This heater draws 20 amps...10 amps per line ( two 110 volt lines gives 220 volts). So 12 gauge wire will work but 10 gauge is better. I also changed the plug to a 220 volt 20 amp one. That works well and does not get hot.', 'I bought this heater as a supplemental heater in my 1500 square foot shop. I am currently running 2 5KW heaters but found that I needed a 3rd when the temp got colder. I was pleasantly surprised with this heater. I was not expecting much  from a heater this inexpensive but have been very pleased. It is much quieter than my other 2 heaters and the heat output is great.', 'The heater works very well but i think the type of plug should have been explained better. I had to buy and install new outlets to plug the heater into.', "I have a cabin that is 30' x 30' with standard 8' ceilings with minimum amount of insulation .This heater does a great job heating it .Not sure about the energy cost as of yet because weather has not been below 30 degrees for more than a few days at a time.", 'The heater works good and gives off good heat. This heater is for getting a room heated up not for just keeping it a certain temp all the time', 'The picture of the plug is not for the EUH5000, it is for the EUH4000, so wait till you receive it before buying the receptacle,it is not dangerous hot but heat enough.', 'Heats my 750 sq foot wood working shop from 25 degrees to 60-62 degrees with an outside temp of 25. column1: Hiland-HLDS01-CGT-Tall Patio Heater With Table Hammered Bronze Finish Open Box
column4: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won‚Äôt light. Very disappointing! I‚Äôm going to see if I can get it serviced since I‚Äôm desperate to have a gas heater for outdoor use for my business.  If I can‚Äôt get it to light, I‚Äôm returning it.', "I purchased it couple of years ago, but after couple of time using it, the heater wouldn't turn on!!! I only used it twice the first year, and it still looks nice but it doesn't work. I didn't realized that I had purchased the 3 year insurance online for it, so when I realized that I have insurance, I filed a claim to get it serviced or replaced, but insurance company was not very helpful, and asked to have it repaired at a certified repair shop, which I didn't find one in OC county, and the other option was to give 50% of the cost!! I rather they would sent a repairman to fix it or replace it!!", 'This was easy to set up and works great! We had one minor issue and that was the latch for the door. It didn‚Äôt come with the bolts for that but no problem a couple small nuts and bolts from my garage and it is awesome!', 'The Items are both working fine so far. My only issue is, one of the items was considerably damaged as you can see in the pictures.', 'Incredible bargain, and very well made. Hot! Hot! Hot1 The assembly is a bit challenging, but worth the effort.', 'As described, very well made, nice looking!', 'Great price.  Works as advertised.  would recommend']

column1: LifeSmart 6 Element Quartz with Wood Cabinet and Remote Infrared Heater - LS-100
column4: ['Pros- Shorter cabinet makes smaller footprint, Nice large easy read temp setting, Looks good, Does a good job heating a coolish 300 sq ft. room.Cons- Shorter cabinet requires faster fan setting I guess. My other larger cabinet one blows slower and much quieter. I really wish it had fan speeds. Lot louder.Tip for the day,Some people complain these heaters wont heat the room. Make sure and close the doors of the room. But the other room is venting warmer air into the cooler room you say. Does not matter close the doors and it will work.', "Great little heater, I live in an apartment I use it in my living room when I get chilled it helps bring my room temperature up so I'm not setting here freezing it really does help for a small space heater it works just like the larger ones it has temperature control it comes with a remote control you can turn it on and off set the temperature I'm using it right now", 'item works great for room heating. they are a very safe heater.  I have 4 of these units in my home plus a wood burning fireplace.  I also have a large heat pump.  no worries about the cold.', 'I bought a life smart heater about 5 years ago and it has been greatly used due to the long winters we have in this part of New York. When it broke this year, I bought the same brand as I felt it was a good value for what we had paid.  It heats quickly and has a strong blower to push the heat in to the room. We run this on a dedicated circuit and find it is very economical.', "Heats well and fan is quiet, turns off when not needed. Warms entire room but portable enough to direct the heat towards a area where i'm sitting.", 'I have one in my living room and one in my basement. My electric bill only went up about 15$ a month. They are a good full time heater or a good spot heater.', "This is the second one of these we've purchased in the last year. Love the digital temp. selector and the remote makes this a very convenient area heater. The oak cabinet makes it blend right in like a piece of furniture. Priced right and a great heater.", "For the price it is a good choice. Doesn't heat as well as the Edenpure it replaced. It is quite and for the money seems well built. Only time will tell if was a good purchase.", 'Heater is good for medium size room. I actually heat about 350 sf of room with it. The thermostat can be set at a comfortable temp and easily changed is easy to use remote.', "I was very leary on buying something that says SAVE MONEY BY LOWERING YOUR HEATING BILL. column1: Dr. Infrared Heater DR-968 1500-watt Portable Space Heater Quiet Fan 1500W
column4: ["Pros-outside of unit not hot if you touch it.it's on wheels, cycles on to adjust set temperature, has a remote, has a timer, safety switches ( temp & if it tips over ). Youtube videos on how to repair unit, parts available. Looks nice, immediate heat, does not deplete oxygen like a ceramic heater, you can breath easily.Cons- 1500 watts & 12.5 amps power used. Monitor it when you first use it, a weak or bad electrical receptacle can arc! Your plug or power cord could melt or burn. The risk always exists when you use it. I use to do electrician work long ago, be mindful.Read all instructions thoroughly and completely! DO NOT LEAVE UNATTENDED! I still like to use this heater, in fact I own two of them. Follow all safety warnings, it can be a good heater, don't let your guard down.....be vigilant, be safe, and stay warm. I watch TV with one keeping me warm, and happy.", "Impressed with quality and many features like holding heat level economically, auto dual fan speeds, easy reading temperature, easy set up and great looking unit. Doesn't even look like a heater, more like a piece of furniture or a speaker for a high end stereo system.", 'I hen purchase several brands of infrared heaters .   Dr. Heater is built solid .  Purchased my last one in 2013.   Warranty is unsurpassed with 3 years .  Most heaters just won‚Äôt last .  Also puts our more heat output than a comparable EdenPure .   Good value and great  quality .', 'It is a hybrid infrared.  60% of the heat comes from a relatively new PTC heater.  40% comes from infrared.  It heats the air and objects in the room at the same time.  I have a small home of 1250 sq. ft.  I have three of these heaters at various places and have been able to shut my gas furnace down entirely.  Since they are very stingy on electricity, my monthly heating bill is now much less than it used to be!  I would recommend this heater to anyone without hesitation!', 'My Dr 968 1500 watt heater produces heat rapidly and cycles on and off to keep the temp where it is set.  This small unit has a fan that is barely audible and manages to push the heat away from the heat elements into the room and keep the area comfortable.  Lots of heat in a small package.', 'Well-built unit. Small, unobtrusive, and quiet. Easy to use with control panel or remote control, and the built-in thermostat works as it should. A nice feature is that the unit is on wheels so makes it easy to roll out of the way when cleaning and vacuuming. Takes the chill off my small place quite nicely. Great to use during those in-between seasons before or after you shut down or turn on the heating system. I am very satisfied with this product!', 'I have read a great deal of reviews from others before my first purchase. I have other brand spot heaters in my collection. Trial by error I suppose. Colorado Winters can be brutal at times. I purchased this for my mothers not well insulated home. a living room and a kitchen connected, 630 sq ft. this heater will keep it at a comfortable temp. for her. All at a low setting.Shuts off as it should to measure the heat in the room and comes back on when it needs to.It is supplemental. It will not heat a whole home.My unit arrived with a cracked frame on the top left corner. It works though, that is my main concern.Stays on five hours as i programmed and shuts off. Good Bang for the Buck. 5200 BTU is a great output for this size The fan is quiet when running. You can watch t.v. without noticing the heater on.In my opinion, if these units are used wisely, they are useful and can save a bit of money on your bill. Thumbs up on this unit.........', "I bought this to use in a bedroom because it was advertised as quiet, and it came with a remote.  It's not that quiet- just a little quieter than your average cheapo space heater.  And the remote doesn't power the heater on or off- just lets the unit go on standby, which is kind of a drag.  The standby light is so bright i wound up covering it with a piece of paper.  Except for the remote, it's not worth the money.", 'Despite the fact that the first heater stopped working after 4 years I purchased another, Reasons: great features, heats area very well, low cost to operate, compact and easy to move around', "Product arrived extremely quickly.  I'm using it in a sun-room to keep the temperatures steady for two parrots.  Am not able to determine if I am saving money on this product or not running it continuously versus other types of heating methods.  Product works well - happy so far."]

Monitor it when you first use it, a weak or bad electrical receptacle can arc! Your plug or power cord could melt or burn. The risk always exists when you use it. I use to do electrician work long ago, be mindful.Read all instructions thoroughly and completely! DO NOT LEAVE UNATTENDED! I still like to use this heater, in fact I own two of them. Follow all safety warnings, it can be a good heater, don't let your guard down.....be vigilant, be safe, and stay warm. I watch TV with one keeping me warm, and happy.", "Impressed with quality and many features like holding heat level economically, auto dual fan speeds, easy reading temperature, easy set up and great looking unit. Doesn't even look like a heater, more like a piece of furniture or a speaker for a high end stereo system.", 'I hen purchase several brands of infrared heaters .   Dr. Heater is built solid .  Purchased my last one in 2013.   Warranty is unsurpassed with 3 years .  Most heaters just won‚Äôt last .  Also puts our more heat output than a comparable EdenPure .   Good value and great  quality .', 'It is a hybrid infrared.  60% of the heat comes from a relatively new PTC heater.  40% comes from infrared.  It heats the air and objects in the room at the same time.  I have a small home of 1250 sq. ft.  I have three of these heaters at various places and have been able to shut my gas furnace down entirely.  Since they are very stingy on electricity, my monthly heating bill is now much less than it used to be!  I would recommend this heater to anyone without hesitation!', 'My Dr 968 1500 watt heater produces heat rapidly and cycles on and off to keep the temp where it is set.  This small unit has a fan that is barely audible and manages to push the heat away from the heat elements into the room and keep the area comfortable.  Lots of heat in a small package.', 'Well-built unit. Small, unobtrusive, and quiet. Easy to use with control panel or remote control, and the built-in thermostat works as it should. A nice feature is that the unit is on wheels so makes it easy to roll out of the way when cleaning and vacuuming. Takes the chill off my small place quite nicely. Great to use during those in-between seasons before or after you shut down or turn on the heating system. I am very satisfied with this product!', 'I have read a great deal of reviews from others before my first purchase. I have other brand spot heaters in my collection. Trial by error I suppose. Colorado Winters can be brutal at times. I purchased this for my mothers not well insulated home. a living room and a kitchen connected, 630 sq ft. this heater will keep it at a comfortable temp. for her. All at a low setting.Shuts off as it should to measure the heat in the room and comes back on when it needs to.It is supplemental. It will not heat a whole home.My unit arrived with a cracked frame on the top left corner. It works though, that is my main concern.Stays on five hours as i programmed and shuts off. Good Bang for the Buck. 5200 BTU is a great output for this size The fan is quiet when running. You can watch t.v. without noticing the heater on.In my opinion, if these units are used wisely, they are useful and can save a bit of money on your bill. Thumbs up on this unit.........', "I bought this to use in a bedroom because it was advertised as quiet, and it came with a remote.  It's not that quiet- just a little quieter than your average cheapo space heater.  And the remote doesn't power the heater on or off- just lets the unit go on standby, which is kind of a drag.  The standby light is so bright i wound up covering it with a piece of paper.  Except for the remote, it's not worth the money.", 'Despite the fact that the first heater stopped working after 4 years I purchased another, Reasons: great features, heats area very well, low cost to operate, compact and easy to move around', "Product arrived extremely quickly.  I'm using it in a sun-room to keep the temperatures steady for two parrots.  Am not able to determine if I am saving money on this product or not running it continuously versus other types of heating methods.  Product works well - happy so far."]

column1: Mr. Heater MH60FAV Forced Air Propane Heater- 60,000 BTU
column4: ["It does a good job of putting out the heat. The only thing that could be better is it's rather noisy and you must unplug it to stop the fan from running. Well worth the price and shipped quickly.", 'Heats my garage better than expected. I‚Äôm no longer a slave to the weather when I want to do my woodworking. PARTY ON AN OPEN PATIO, HELPED TAKE THE CHILL OFF.', "I'm happy so far with my purchase but i have only used the heater twice in my garage so far this year.", 'I replaced my older heater with this one, this one produces much more heat much faster. Would recommend']

column1: Ceramic Heater w Remote
column4: ["this little heater will heat your small room to a toasty comfort level in just minutes, with the remote control everything is a snap and no need to get out of your seat, it is that easy to use, it's compact so it fits anywhere in a room giving you space, this product was a really good price,", "I love this heater. My wife dragged me to Lowe's to by a heater. I told her that we should buy a ceramic heater instead of a infrared heater. But like always she didn't want to listen. We ended up buying a heater for 150. This heater looks like old cast iron heater and it takes like an hour to make a room comfy. BBUUUUTTTT this Lasko heater is the BOMB and very worth it.", "Works like a champ.  This heats my 250 square foot garage that is like an ice cube, otherwise.  I really like the thermostat feature.  I've had two of these in the past, and they have always worked well.", "We have a small house in s.e. mich.. about 700 sq. ft. on the main level.  several years ago our furnace quit and we've been using ceramic heaters ever since.  I bought this lasco heater this fall to see if it could do better than the previous heater and it has been keeping the wholehouseat about 66 to 68 degrees so far.  Right now we are having the coldest below zero weather in years and it is still keeping things at around 60 with no other heater. needless to say, we have turned on an additional ceramic heater and the temp in the living room isaround 65. I repeat we have no other furnace or heater in the housethe basement stays around 60 all the time but as soon as the outdoors temps rise into the 20's and 30's it will be about 68 in here and we will only need the large Lasco heater.I am very happy with this heater.", 'Works well and looks like the picture, but not quite the remote I was looking for.  I understand the remote that actually went with my upright fan, the model is now out of date or for sale.', 'I plugged the space heaters in immediately and it took the chill right off the house love them. I have a heat pump and when the temperature gets below 32 the system needs help. These are perfect.', 'Quiet; Very powerful; Many fan & heat speed/temperature options. Delivered much faster than even my dog\'s favorite (E-bay) dog food! The back of this unit is not even the slightest bit warm, even when temperature and fan speed are at "max"! Greatly helps supplement our home\'s central heat, even during extremely cold weather.', "This heater warms my apartment way better than the heating sytem for the apartment. It's easy to move around and it does not get hot so you can move it without the danger of getting burned bu holding the sides. Good choice for anyone who has to use gas heat or heat a lot. Could save you a lot of money.", 'Actually, my 5/6 year old unit is STILL GOOD. but the remote died from battery corrosion.So, I now have TWO GOOD EXCELLENT HEATERS- with One REMOTE. * works on bothüëçüèª', "This heater provides a great deal of heat for a large room/ recommend it for purchase, if a person is interested a quality heater.....it's well worth the investment/ Thank you."]

column1: Hiland-HLDS01-CGT-Tall Patio Heater With Table Hammered Bronze Finish Open Box
column4: ['The heater was quick to put together. Be careful when assembling the heat shield, it has sharp edges. After I assembled it, I attached an extra propane tank for my gas grill. I followed the simple lighting instructions and it fired right up. The cocktail table is a nice touch, but the ice in drinks will melt quickly with the amount of heat it gives off. The finish and appearance is very nice, I also bought a heater cover to protect it against the elements when it is not is use. The only complaint is, the door hatch for the propane storage is a little wonky when closing and securing it. Overall I highly recommend it.', "It's a little harder to start than others we have used, but is large, nice looking, and cozy to hang out by! Puts off a lot of heat...recommend, though I have found others at better prices.", "I had promised my wife a heater on the new porch ASAP.  There was nothing affordable local.  The big box stores had zero stock and no way to order.  Then I came across AZ Patio Heaters, asking a reasonable price for a 48KBtu heater.  Shipping was extraordinarily fast.  Package came with no dents.  Assembly relatively easy - I mean, there is some dexterity involved, but it wasn't difficult.  Unit immediately fired up.We'll be using it all winter into the spring.  ", 'It came on time.  Easy to put together but the pilot won‚Äôt light. Very disappointing! I‚Äôm going to see if I can get it serviced since I‚Äôm desperate to have a gas heater for outdoor use for my business.  If I can‚Äôt get it to light, I‚Äôm returning it.', "I purchased it couple of years ago, but after couple of time using it, the heater wouldn't turn on!!! I only used it twice the first year, and it still looks nice but it doesn't work. I didn't realized that I had purchased the 3 year insurance online for it, so when I realized that I have insurance, I filed a claim to get it serviced or replaced, but insurance company was not very helpful, and asked to have it repaired at a certified repair shop, which I didn't find one in OC county, and the other option was to give 50% of the cost!! I rather they would sent a repairman to fix it or replace it!!", 'This was easy to set up and works great! We had one minor issue and that was the latch for the door. It didn‚Äôt come with the bolts for that but no problem a couple small nuts and bolts from my garage and it is awesome!', 'The Items are both working fine so far. My only issue is, one of the items was considerably damaged as you can see in the pictures.', 'Incredible bargain, and very well made. Hot! Hot! Hot1 The assembly is a bit challenging, but worth the effort.', 'As described, very well made, nice looking!', 'Great price.  Works as advertised.  would recommend']

column1: Broan/nautilus 174 750/1500W White Painted Grill Wall Heater
column4: ['We bought two heaters by different manufacturers in order to compare. This one is quieter and heats better. The thermostat works better and is more accurate. Great unit, it keeps a 230 square foot room warm even in 10 degree F weather.', 'I bought this heater to replace the same one I installed in my lower level bathroom 20 years ago. The replacement was exactly the same size which made the replacement of the internal parts in the existing sheet metal frame very fast. It works well for this small bath to take the chill of the lower level out between heating seasons. After removing the existing Broan 174 I saw a build up of lint/dust on the back side of the heater eliment and it may not have been bad to begin with, so I will keep that in mind if it starts smelling hot (In the next 20 years). Bottom line is it work well to heat a small room quickly.', 'Very good to use in a small bathroom,I run it 240v for less power consumption ', 'it was exactly what I wanted --keeps my small bathroom very warm', 'Easy to install, heat is fast, fan is quiet, looks great.', 'This is the 5th of these heaters I have purchased.  Mostly used in bathrooms and bedrooms both in my own home and in rental properties.  They are reliable, and very quiet, put forth plenty of gentle warm heat without worrying if a small child is close to them.  Excellent product.', 'this heater does exactly what it is build to do .and the support is great and will work well with you.', 'Good quality heater.  Easy to install.  I have four of these and all work perfectly.', 'Thermostat shuts the heater off too soon.', 'small and heats good']

column1: LifeSmart 6 Element Quartz with Wood Cabinet and Remote Infrared Heater - LS-100
column4: ['Pros- Shorter cabinet makes smaller footprint, Nice large easy read temp setting, Looks good, Does a good job heating a coolish 300 sq ft. room.Cons- Shorter cabinet requires faster fan setting I guess. My other larger cabinet one blows slower and much quieter. I really wish it had fan speeds. Lot louder.Tip for the day,Some people complain these heaters wont heat the room. Make sure and close the doors of the room. But the other room is venting warmer air into the cooler room you say. Does not matter close the doors and it will work.', "Great little heater, I live in an apartment I use it in my living room when I get chilled it helps bring my room temperature up so I'm not setting here freezing it really does help for a small space heater it works just like the larger ones it has temperature control it comes with a remote control you can turn it on and off set the temperature I'm using it right now", 'item works great for room heating. they are a very safe heater.  I have 4 of these units in my home plus a wood burning fireplace.  I also have a large heat pump.  no worries about the cold.', 'I bought a life smart heater about 5 years ago and it has been greatly used due to the long winters we have in this part of New York. When it broke this year, I bought the same brand as I felt it was a good value for what we had paid.  It heats quickly and has a strong blower to push the heat in to the room. We run this on a dedicated circuit and find it is very economical.', "Heats well and fan is quiet, turns off when not needed. Warms entire room but portable enough to direct the heat towards a area where i'm sitting.", 'I have one in my living room and one in my basement. My electric bill only went up about 15$ a month. They are a good full time heater or a good spot heater.', "This is the second one of these we've purchased in the last year. Love the digital temp. selector and the remote makes this a very convenient area heater. The oak cabinet makes it blend right in like a piece of furniture. Priced right and a great heater.", "For the price it is a good choice. Doesn't heat as well as the Edenpure it replaced. It is quite and for the money seems well built. Only time will tell if was a good purchase.", 'Heater is good for medium size room. I actually heat about 350 sf of room with it. The thermostat can be set at a comfortable temp and easily changed is easy to use remote.', "I was very leary on buying something that says SAVE MONEY BY LOWERING YOUR HEATING BILL. column1: Dr. Infrared Heater DR-968 1500-watt Portable Space Heater Quiet Fan 1500W
column4: ["Pros-outside of unit not hot if you touch it.it's on wheels, cycles on to adjust set temperature, has a remote, has a timer, safety switches ( temp & if it tips over ). Youtube videos on how to repair unit, parts available. Looks nice, immediate heat, does not deplete oxygen like a ceramic heater, you can breath easily.Cons- 1500 watts & 12.5 amps power used. Monitor it when you first use it, a weak or bad electrical receptacle can arc! Your plug or power cord could melt or burn. The risk always exists when you use it. I use to do electrician work long ago, be mindful.Read all instructions thoroughly and completely! DO NOT LEAVE UNATTENDED! I still like to use this heater, in fact I own two of them. Follow all safety warnings, it can be a good heater, don't let your guard down.....be vigilant, be safe, and stay warm. I watch TV with one keeping me warm, and happy.", "Impressed with quality and many features like holding heat level economically, auto dual fan speeds, easy reading temperature, easy set up and great looking unit. Doesn't even look like a heater, more like a piece of furniture or a speaker for a high end stereo system.", 'I hen purchase several brands of infrared heaters .   Dr. Heater is built solid .  Purchased my last one in 2013.   Warranty is unsurpassed with 3 years .  Most heaters just won‚Äôt last .  Also puts our more heat output than a comparable EdenPure .   Good value and great  quality .', 'It is a hybrid infrared.  60% of the heat comes from a relatively new PTC heater.  40% comes from infrared.  It heats the air and objects in the room at the same time.  I have a small home of 1250 sq. ft.  I have three of these heaters at various places and have been able to shut my gas furnace down entirely.  Since they are very stingy on electricity, my monthly heating bill is now much less than it used to be!  I would recommend this heater to anyone without hesitation!', 'My Dr 968 1500 watt heater produces heat rapidly and cycles on and off to keep the temp where it is set.  This small unit has a fan that is barely audible and manages to push the heat away from the heat elements into the room and keep the area comfortable.  Lots of heat in a small package.', 'Well-built unit. Small, unobtrusive, and quiet. Easy to use with control panel or remote control, and the built-in thermostat works as it should. A nice feature is that the unit is on wheels so makes it easy to roll out of the way when cleaning and vacuuming. Takes the chill off my small place quite nicely. Great to use during those in-between seasons before or after you shut down or turn on the heating system. I am very satisfied with this product!', 'I have read a great deal of reviews from others before my first purchase. I have other brand spot heaters in my collection. Trial by error I suppose. Colorado Winters can be brutal at times. I purchased this for my mothers not well insulated home. a living room and a kitchen connected, 630 sq ft. this heater will keep it at a comfortable temp. for her. All at a low setting.Shuts off as it should to measure the heat in the room and comes back on when it needs to.It is supplemental. It will not heat a whole home.My unit arrived with a cracked frame on the top left corner. It works though, that is my main concern.Stays on five hours as i programmed and shuts off. Good Bang for the Buck. 5200 BTU is a great output for this size The fan is quiet when running. You can watch t.v. without noticing the heater on.In my opinion, if these units are used wisely, they are useful and can save a bit of money on your bill. Thumbs up on this unit.........', "I bought this to use in a bedroom because it was advertised as quiet, and it came with a remote.  It's not that quiet- just a little quieter than your average cheapo space heater.  And the remote doesn't power the heater on or off- just lets the unit go on standby, which is kind of a drag.  The standby light is so bright i wound up covering it with a piece of paper.  Except for the remote, it's not worth the money.", 'Despite the fact that the first heater stopped working after 4 years I purchased another, Reasons: great features, heats area very well, low cost to operate, compact and easy to move around', "Product arrived extremely quickly.  I'm using it in a sun-room to keep the temperatures steady for two parrots.  Am not able to determine if I am saving money on this product or not running it continuously versus other types of heating methods.  Product works well - happy so far."]

column1: Ceramic Heater w Remote
column4: ["this little heater will heat your small room to a toasty comfort level in just minutes, with the remote control everything is a snap and no need to get out of your seat, it is that easy to use, it's compact so it fits anywhere in a room giving you space, this product was a really good price,", "I love this heater. My wife dragged me to Lowe's to by a heater. I told her that we should buy a ceramic heater instead of a infrared heater. But like always she didn't want to listen. We ended up buying a heater for 150. This heater looks like old cast iron heater and it takes like an hour to make a room comfy. BBUUUUTTTT this Lasko heater is the BOMB and very worth it.", "Works like a champ.  This heats my 250 square foot garage that is like an ice cube, otherwise.  I really like the thermostat feature.  I've had two of these in the past, and they have always worked well.", "We have a small house in s.e. mich.. about 700 sq. ft. on the main level.  several years ago our furnace quit and we've been using ceramic heaters ever since.  I bought this lasco heater this fall to see if it could do better than the previous heater and it has been keeping the wholehouseat about 66 to 68 degrees so far.  Right now we are having the coldest below zero weather in years and it is still keeping things at around 60 with no other heater. needless to say, we have turned on an additional ceramic heater and the temp in the living room isaround 65. I repeat we have no other furnace or heater in the housethe basement stays around 60 all the time but as soon as the outdoors temps rise into the 20's and 30's it will be about 68 in here and we will only need the large Lasco heater.I am very happy with this heater.", 'Works well and looks like the picture, but not quite the remote I was looking for.  I understand the remote that actually went with my upright fan, the model is now out of date or for sale.', 'I plugged the space heaters in immediately and it took the chill right off the house love them. I have a heat pump and when the temperature gets below 32 the system needs help. These are perfect.', 'Quiet; Very powerful; Many fan & heat speed/temperature options. Delivered much faster than even my dog\'s favorite (E-bay) dog food! The back of this unit is not even the slightest bit warm, even when temperature and fan speed are at "max"! Greatly helps supplement our home\'s central heat, even during extremely cold weather.', "This heater warms my apartment way better than the heating sytem for the apartment. It's easy to move around and it does not get hot so you can move it without the danger of getting burned bu holding the sides. Good choice for anyone who has to use gas heat or heat a lot. Could save you a lot of money.", 'Actually, my 5/6 year old unit is STILL GOOD. but the remote died from battery corrosion.So, I now have TWO GOOD EXCELLENT HEATERS- with One REMOTE. * works on bothüëçüèª', "This heater provides a great deal of heat for a large room/ recommend it for purchase, if a person is interested a quality heater.....it's well worth the investment/ Thank you."]

column1: Cadet Electric Wall Heater 9" W x 12.0" H Corrosion Resistant Thermostat White
column4: ["It was replacing an aged wall heater that had finally given up the ghost. It was a 1500 watt model, but after installing the Com-Pak, that was only 1000 watts, it's output was higher. And it's construction was obviously of high higher quality.  And it is much quieter than old was, even when it was new. Only problem I had was it was slightly smaller to fit into the original hole in the wall.  Not the fault of the heater. I'm a bit of a handy-man so just shimmed the hole and trimmed it with some molding and it looks pretty good.", 'I have been dealing with electrical items and electricity for 60 years, andthis heater beats any I have ever dealt with. To be as small as it is, easy to mount,,but the most important thing is 2000 watts and only pulling 8.3 amps seems unreal. Most electric heaters 120 v, 1500 watts pull 12...I have just ordered another one and plan on another.
